Direct headaches will have their origin within your head and may relate to stress, chemical changes within your brain, food reactions, or other causes. Headaches can often be referred from your cervical spine (neck), your mid to upper back and your jaw. Referred headaches can often relate to poor posture, or inadequate flexibility or stability around the neck.<\\\/p><p>Regardless of the potential issues at play, we specialize in thorough analysis and assessment. Our clinicians identify issues and develop treatment programs to deliver effective outcomes.<\\\/p><p><b>Common conditions :<\\\/b><\\\/p><p>The head and neck are complex interrelated structures comprising intricate networks of discs, ligaments, vessels and vertebrae. As a result, there can be multiple factors contributing to head or neck pain. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"postmeta","row":{"meta_id":"4336","post_id":"2538","meta_key":"fw:opt:ext:pb:page-builder:json","meta_value":"[{\"type\":\"simple\",\"shortcode\":\"divider\",\"atts\":{\"style\":{\"ruler_type\":\"\",\"space\":{\"height\":\"50\"}}}},{\"type\":\"column\",\"_items\":[],\"width\":\"1_1\",\"atts\":{\"column_layout\":\"\"}},{\"type\":\"simple\",\"shortcode\":\"text_block\",\"atts\":{\"text\":\"<h1>Treatment<\\\/h1><p>Headaches can be caused by multiple issues and may be direct or referred in nature. Direct headaches will have their origin within your head and may relate to stress, chemical changes within your brain, food reactions, or other causes. Headaches can often be referred from your cervical spine (neck), your mid to upper back and your jaw. Referred headaches can often relate to poor posture, or inadequate flexibility or stability around the neck.<\\\/p><p>Regardless of the potential issues at play, we specialize in thorough analysis and assessment. Our clinicians identify issues and develop treatment programs to deliver effective outcomes.<\\\/p><p><b>Common conditions :<\\\/b><\\\/p><p>The head and neck are complex interrelated structures comprising intricate networks of discs, ligaments, vessels and vertebrae. As a result, there can be multiple factors contributing to head or neck pain. Some of the more common conditions we treat include post-surgical rehabilitation, disc problems, stiffness, facet joint dysfunction, neck related headaches, postural problems, acute sprains and strains, osteoarthritis and arm pain referring from the neck.<\\\/p>\"}},{\"type\":\"simple\",\"shortcode\":\"text_block\",\"atts\":{\"text\":\"\"}}]"}}}

Direct headaches will have their origin within your head and may relate to stress, chemical changes within your brain, food reactions, or other causes. Headaches can often be referred from your cervical spine (neck), your mid to upper back and your jaw. Referred headaches can often relate to poor posture, or inadequate flexibility or stability around the neck.<\\\/p><p>Regardless of the potential issues at play, we specialize in thorough analysis and assessment. Our clinicians identify issues and develop treatment programs to deliver effective outcomes.<\\\/p><p><b>Common conditions :<\\\/b><\\\/p><p>The head and neck are complex interrelated structures comprising intricate networks of discs, ligaments, vessels and vertebrae. As a result, there can be multiple factors contributing to head or neck pain. This included but wasn't limited to:<\\\/p><p><b>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:<\\\/b>\\u00a0This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the American Academy of Manipulative Therapy\\\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\\\/ Dry Needling Institute. After multiple written, oral and practical examinations and earning Certification in Dry Needling (Cert. DN), Certification in Spinal Manipulative Therapy (Cert. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\\\/DO\\\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors.<\\\/p><p><b>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:<\\\/b>\\u00a0This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT). After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State.<\\\/p><p><b>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:<\\\/b>\\u00a0The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force. After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques.<\\\/p><p><b>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY<\\\/b>\\u00a0( AAMT\\\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT. Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.<\\\/p>\"}}],\"width\":\"2_3\",\"atts\":{\"column_layout\":\"\"}}]"}}}

Osteopractic Fellowship Trained in OMT<\\\/p><p class=\\\"bottommargin_10\\\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance. Dr. Stanislawski\\u2019s unique style is influenced by several OMT (Orthopaedic Manual\\\/Manipulative Therapy) systems he studied. This included but wasn't limited to:<\\\/p><p><b>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:<\\\/b>\\u00a0This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the American Academy of Manipulative Therapy\\\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\\\/ Dry Needling Institute. After multiple written, oral and practical examinations and earning Certification in Dry Needling (Cert. DN), Certification in Spinal Manipulative Therapy (Cert. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\\\/DO\\\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors.<\\\/p><p><b>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:<\\\/b>\\u00a0This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT). After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State.<\\\/p><p><b>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:<\\\/b>\\u00a0The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force. After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques.<\\\/p><p><b>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY<\\\/b>\\u00a0( AAMT\\\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT. Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.<\\\/p>\"}}],\"width\":\"2_3\",\"atts\":{\"column_layout\":\"\"}}]"}}}

Headaches can often be referred from your cervical spine (neck), your mid to upper back and your jaw. Referred headaches can often relate to poor posture, or inadequate flexibility or stability around the neck.<\\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nRegardless of the potential issues at play, we specialize in thorough analysis and assessment. Our clinicians identify issues and develop treatment programs to deliver effective outcomes.<\\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<b>Common conditions :<\\\/b>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\nThe head and neck are complex interrelated structures comprising intricate networks of discs, ligaments, vessels and vertebrae. As a result, there can be multiple factors contributing to head or neck pain. Some of the more common conditions we treat include post-surgical rehabilitation, disc problems, stiffness, facet joint dysfunction, neck related headaches, postural problems, acute sprains and strains, osteoarthritis and arm pain referring from the neck.<\\\/p>\"},{\"tab_title\":\"Shoulder\",\"tab_content\":\"Like every patient we see, we treat every shoulder issue on a case by case basis. We tailor our approach to meet your specific individual needs. We\\u2019ll obtain a full overview to determine the issue: the location and type of pain, the mechanism of injury, any aggravating factors, easing factors, contributing lifestyle factors, and your personal goals for rehabilitation. Then, we get to work.\\r\\n\\r\\n<b>Common conditions :<\\\/b>\\r\\n\\r\\nShoulder pain can be linked to a range of injuries, and resolution may require treatment to your shoulder, back and neck. Some of the more frequent conditions that present in clinic are postural dysfunctions or problems, post-surgical rehabilitation, tendon impingement, shoulder bursitis, acute joint soft tissue injuries, rotator cuff dysfunction, rotator cuff tears, AC joint injuries, and post-fracture rehabilitation.\"}],\"btn_label\":\"\",\"btn_link\":\"#\",\"acc_type\":\"acc-type1\"}}]"}}}

{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"1","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-08-22 13:18:04","post_date_gmt":"2016-08-22 13:18:04","post_content":"With summer in full swing, everyone is out exploring, adventuring, and being active in their daily life. However, stretching after their physical activity is often overlooked. Many people forget about stretching, even those that are normally considered \u201cactive\u201d individuals. Developing good stretching habits can help to improve flexibility and performance, especially in sports and other physical activities.\r\n\r\n<strong>Greatly Improves Flexibility<\/strong>\r\n\r\nConsistent stretch habits can improve an individual\u2019s overall flexibility over time. This allows them to perform more efficiently during their sport or other physically demanding activity. Flexibility is important because it increase the range at which you can move each limb, allowing you to twist and reach further than you could without stretching.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reduces the Risk of Injury<\/strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-2089\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_97979030_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_97979030_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>Stretching safely exposes your body to the strenuous limits that your sport or activity may introduce. By stretching in advance, it \u201cprepares\u201d the body for meeting those limits as they occur by loosening up the muscles slowly and carefully. Without stretching, if your muscle is forced to endure certain limits (typically very quickly and strongly), it can cause damage to the muscles. Stretching in advance will reduce the risk of injury because the muscle is already \u201cprepared\u201d for that exertion of force.\r\n\r\n<strong>Increases Blood Flow for Performance<\/strong>\r\n\r\nNot only does stretching improve flexibility and reduce the risk of injury, it will also help to improve the flow of blood through your body and the stretched muscles. Improved blood flow can help to improve overall performance, because each muscle is receiving more blood to help it perform more effectively.\r\n\r\n<strong>Quick Tips for Stretching<\/strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2081 alignleft\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_78288658_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_78288658_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>Stretching doesn\u2019t need to be complicated, but it should be worked into your exercising routine or before\/after any physical activities.\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Stretch major muscle groups, especially the areas you expect to use during your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Hold the stretch for a period of time (e.g., 30-60 seconds).<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Breathe normally during your stretching sessions.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Aim for tension, but not for pain during your stretches.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Keep movements smooth and avoid bouncing.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Tailor your stretches for your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Stay consistent with your stretching habits (e.g., a few times per week).<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTry these tips out and incorporate stretching into your daily life \u2013 in addition to your sports and physical activities!","post_title":"Improves Flexibility","post_excerpt":"With summer in full swing, everyone is out exploring, adventuring, and being active in their daily life. However, stretching after their physical activity is often overlooked. Many people forget about stretching, even those that are normally considered \u201cactive\u201d individuals. \u0438\u0437\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043a\u0430\u0442\u043e Aldus PageMaker, \u043a\u043e\u0439\u0442\u043e \u0432\u043a\u043b\u044e\u0447\u0432\u0430 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u0438 \u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043d\u0430 Lorem Ipsum.\n\nCatal\u00e0\n\nLorem Ipsum \u00e9s un text de farciment usat per la ind\u00fastria de la tipografia i la impremta. Lorem Ipsum ha estat el text est\u00e0ndard de la ind\u00fastria des de l'any 1500, quan un impressor desconegut va fer servir una galerada de text i la va mesclar per crear un llibre de mostres tipogr\u00e0fiques. No nom\u00e9s ha sobreviscut cinc segles, sin\u00f3 que ha fet el salt cap a la creaci\u00f3 de tipus de lletra electr\u00f2nics, romanent essencialment sense canvis. Es va popularitzar l'any 1960 amb el llan\u00e7ament de fulls Letraset que contenien passatges de Lorem Ipsum, i m\u00e9s recentment amb programari d'autoedici\u00f3 com Aldus Pagemaker que inclou versions de Lorem Ipsum.\n\nHrvatski\n\nLorem Ipsum je jednostavno probni tekst koji se koristi u tiskarskoj i slovoslagarskoj industriji. Lorem Ipsum postoji kao industrijski standard jo\u0161 od 16-og stolje\u0107a, kada je nepoznati tiskar uzeo tiskarsku galiju slova i poslo\u017eio ih da bi napravio knjigu s uzorkom tiska. Taj je tekst ne samo pre\u017eivio pet stolje\u0107a, ve\u0107 se i vinuo u svijet elektronskog slovoslagarstva, ostaju\u0107i u su\u0161tini nepromijenjen. Postao je popularan tijekom 1960-ih s pojavom Letraset listova s odlomcima Lorem Ipsum-a, a u skorije vrijeme sa software-om za stolno izdava\u0161tvo kao \u0161to je Aldus PageMaker koji tako\u0111er sadr\u017ei varijante Lorem Ipsum-a.\n\n\u010cesky\n\nLorem Ipsum je demonstrativn\u00ed v\u00fdpl\u0148ov\u00fd text pou\u017e\u00edvan\u00fd v tiska\u0159sk\u00e9m a kniha\u0159sk\u00e9m pr\u016fmyslu. Lorem Ipsum je pova\u017eov\u00e1no za standard v t\u00e9to oblasti u\u017e od za\u010d\u00e1tku 16. stolet\u00ed, kdy dnes nezn\u00e1m\u00fd tiska\u0159 vzal kusy textu a na jejich z\u00e1klad\u011b vytvo\u0159il speci\u00e1ln\u00ed vzorovou knihu. Jeho odkaz nevydr\u017eel pouze p\u011bt stolet\u00ed, on p\u0159e\u017eil i n\u00e1stup elektronick\u00e9 sazby v podstat\u011b beze zm\u011bny. Nejv\u00edce popularizov\u00e1no bylo Lorem Ipsum v \u0161edes\u00e1t\u00fdch letech 20. stolet\u00ed, kdy byly vyd\u00e1v\u00e1ny speci\u00e1ln\u00ed vzorn\u00edky s jeho pas\u00e1\u017eemi a pozd\u011bji pak d\u00edky po\u010d\u00edta\u010dov\u00fdm DTP program\u016fm jako Aldus PageMaker.\n\nRom\u00e2na\n\nLorem Ipsum este pur \u015fi simplu o machet\u0103 pentru text a industriei tipografice. Lorem Ipsum a fost macheta standard a industriei \u00eenc\u0103 din secolul al XVI-lea, c\u00e2nd un tipograf anonim a luat o plan\u015fet\u0103 de litere \u015fi le-a amestecat pentru a crea o carte demonstrativ\u0103 pentru literele respective. Nu doar c\u0103 a supravie\u0163uit timp de cinci secole, dar \u015fi a facut saltul \u00een tipografia electronic\u0103 practic neschimbat\u0103. A fost popularizat\u0103 \u00een anii '60 odat\u0103 cu ie\u015firea colilor Letraset care con\u0163ineau pasaje Lorem Ipsum, iar mai recent, prin programele de publicare pentru calculator, ca Aldus PageMaker care includeau versiuni de Lorem Ipsum.\n\n\u0421\u0440\u043f\u0441\u043a\u0438\n\nLorem Ipsum \u0458\u0435 \u0458\u0435\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e \u043c\u043e\u0434\u0435\u043b \u0442\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0458\u0438 \u0441\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0443 \u0448\u0442\u0430\u043c\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0458 \u0438 \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0447\u043a\u043e\u0458 \u0438\u043d\u0434\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0458\u0438. Lorem ipsum \u0458\u0435 \u0431\u0438\u043e \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0434 \u0437\u0430 \u043c\u043e\u0434\u0435\u043b \u0442\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u0458\u043e\u0448 \u0431\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u043e \u0443\u0437\u043e\u0440\u0430\u043a \u043a\u045a\u0438\u0433\u0435. \u041d\u0435 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e \u0448\u0442\u043e \u0458\u0435 \u043e\u0432\u0430\u0458 \u043c\u043e\u0434\u0435\u043b \u043e\u043f\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043e \u043f\u0435\u0442 \u0432\u0435\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430, \u043d\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0458\u0435 \u0441\u0435. \u041f\u043e\u043f\u0443\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d \u0458\u0435 \u0448\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0445 {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"1133","post_author":"2","post_date":"2013-03-15 18:19:23","post_date_gmt":"2013-03-15 23:19:23","post_content":"Welcome to image alignment! The best way to demonstrate the ebb and flow of the various image positioning options is to nestle them snuggly among an ocean of words. Grab a paddle and let's get started.\n\nOn the topic of alignment, it should be noted that users can choose from the options of\u00a0<em>None<\/em>,\u00a0<em>Left<\/em>,\u00a0<em>Right, <\/em>and\u00a0<em>Center<\/em>. In addition, they also get the options of\u00a0<em>Thumbnail<\/em>,\u00a0<em>Medium<\/em>,\u00a0<em>Large<\/em>\u00a0&amp;\u00a0<em>Fullsize<\/em>.\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-906 aligncenter\" title=\"Image Alignment 580x300\" alt=\"Image Alignment 580x300\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/03\/image-alignment-580x300.jpg\" width=\"580\" height=\"300\" \/><\/p>\nThe image above happens to be\u00a0<em><strong>centered<\/strong><\/em>.\n\n<strong><img class=\"size-full wp-image-904 alignleft\" title=\"Image Alignment 150x150\" alt=\"Image Alignment 150x150\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/03\/image-alignment-150x150.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" \/><\/strong>The rest of this paragraph is filler\u00a0for the sake of seeing the text wrap around the 150x150 image, which is <em><strong>left aligned<\/strong><\/em>.\u00a0<strong><\/strong>\n\nAs you can see the should be some space above, below, and to the right of the image. The text should not be creeping on the image. Creeping is just not right. Images need breathing room too. Let them speak like you words. Let them do their jobs without any hassle from the text. In about one more\u00a0sentence\u00a0here, we'll see that the text moves from the right of the image down below the image in\u00a0seamless\u00a0transition. Again, letting the do it's thang.\u00a0Mission accomplished!\n\nAnd now for a <em><strong>massively large image<\/strong><\/em>. It also has <em><strong>no alignment<\/strong><\/em>.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-907\" title=\"Image Alignment 1200x400\" alt=\"Image Alignment 1200x400\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/03\/image-alignment-1200x4002.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"400\" \/>\n\nThe image above, though 1200px wide, should not overflow the content area. It should remain contained with no visible disruption to the flow of content.\n\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-905 alignright\" title=\"Image Alignment 300x200\" alt=\"Image Alignment 300x200\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/03\/image-alignment-300x200.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>\n\nAnd now we're going to shift things to the <em><strong>right align<\/strong><\/em>. Again, there should be plenty of room above, below, and to the left of the image. Just look at him there... Hey guy! Way to rock that right side. I don't care what the left aligned image says, you look great. Don't let anyone else tell you differently.\n\nIn just a bit here, you should see the text start to wrap below the right aligned image and settle in nicely. There should still be plenty of room and everything should be sitting pretty.\u00a0Yeah... Just like that. It never felt so good to be right.\n\nAnd just when you thought we were done, we're going to do them all over again with captions!\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_906\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"580\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-906  \" title=\"Image Alignment 580x300\" alt=\"Image Alignment 580x300\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/03\/image-alignment-580x300.jpg\" width=\"580\" height=\"300\" \/> Look at 580x300 getting some <a title=\"Image Settings\" href=\"http:\/\/en.support.wordpress.com\/images\/image-settings\/\">caption<\/a> love.[\/caption]\n\nThe image above happens to be\u00a0<em><strong>centered<\/strong><\/em>. There should still be plenty of room and everything should be sitting pretty. Yeah... Just like that. It never felt so good to be right.\n\nAnd that's a wrap, yo! {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"1707","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-08-26 09:55:05","post_date_gmt":"2016-08-26 09:55:05","post_content":"<section class=\"ls section_padding_50 columns_padding_25\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 text-center\">\r\n<h2 class=\"section_header\">Got Questions? We've Got Answers!<\/h2>\r\nAnswers to the most frequently asked questions.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div class=\"row vertical-tabs\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-5\">\r\n\r\n<!-- Nav tabs -->\r\n<ul class=\"nav\" role=\"tablist\">\r\n \t<li class=\"active\"><a role=\"tab\" href=\"faq2.html#vertical-tab1\" data-toggle=\"tab\">Why Us?<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li><a role=\"tab\" href=\"faq2.html#vertical-tab2\" data-toggle=\"tab\">How are my problems diagnosed?<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li><a role=\"tab\" href=\"faq2.html#vertical-tab3\" data-toggle=\"tab\">How long will my recovery take?<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li><a role=\"tab\" href=\"faq2.html#vertical-tab4\" data-toggle=\"tab\">What are the steps involved in treatment ?<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li><a role=\"tab\" href=\"faq2.html#vertical-tab5\" data-toggle=\"tab\">What can I do in the meantime if I\u2019m suffering from pain or loss of function?<\/a><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-7\">\r\n\r\n<!-- Tab panes -->\r\n<div class=\"tab-content no-border\">\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab1\" class=\"tab-pane fade in active\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">Why Us?<\/h3>\r\nWe are a team of orthopaedic Physical Therapists dedicated to quality care. We are privileged to be located in one office space with two orthopaedic surgeons and a Doctor of Podiatric Medicine with whom we cooperate very closely to ensure that your rehabilitative and therapeutic needs are fully met. We also have a professional relationship with doctors specializing in Pain Management. This ensures a comprehensive orthopaedic and rehabilitative care.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab2\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">How are my problems diagnosed?<\/h3>\r\nDiagnosis involves a careful, comprehensive assessment. This incorporates medical history, physical examination, and medical tests like MRIs, x-rays or ultrasound (depending on the patient and issue). Our doctor will be able to determine diagnosis and create a treatment plan. If required, we can recommend you to a specialist for additional examination and insight.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab3\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">How long will my recovery take?<\/h3>\r\nAcute low back pain or neck pain is usually treated very successfully within two or three sessions. Postoperative and chronic problems require a longer treatment time. Every case is different, and every person will respond to rehabilitation and treatment differently. You\u2019ll have a much better understanding of your recovery timeframe after meeting with one of our doctors; establishing a clear diagnosis and relating it to your unique goals.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab4\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">What are the steps involved in treatment ?<\/h3>\r\nOne common component of treatment is manual therapy, which is used to regain normal joint mobility and to release tight or overactive muscle and connective tissue. This is essential in recapturing optimal tissue flexibility and joint fluidity.\r\n\r\n<b>In addition, treatment commonly includes:<\/b>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Dedicated rehabilitative exercises including postural corrective exercises.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Ergonomic\/workplace condition assessment.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Newest and cutting edge equipment like laser, ultrasound, electrical stimulation.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Recommendations for ongoing improvement.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab5\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">What can I do in the meantime if I\u2019m suffering from pain or loss of function?<\/h3>\r\nAvoid any activity that aggravates the affected area. Get in touch with your doctor or with one of our doctors as soon as possible to book a detailed assessment.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab6\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">Justo duo dolores et ea rebum?<\/h3>\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"1870","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-02 18:34:38","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-02 18:34:38","post_content":"<h2 class=\"section_header\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/h2>\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">DPT, FAAOMPT, Dip. Osteopractic Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n<p class=\"bottommargin_10\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance. Dr. Stanislawski\u2019s unique style is influenced by several OMT (Orthopaedic Manual\/Manipulative Therapy) systems he studied. This included but wasn't limited to:<\/p>\r\n<b>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:<\/b> This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the American Academy of Manipulative Therapy\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\/ Dry Needling Institute. After multiple written, oral and practical examinations and earning Certification in Dry Needling (Cert. DN), Certification in Spinal Manipulative Therapy (Cert. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\/DO\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors.\r\n\r\n<!-- Nav tabs -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Tab panes -->\r\n\r\n<b>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:<\/b> This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT). After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State.\r\n\r\n<b>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:<\/b> The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force. After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques.\r\n\r\n<b>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY<\/b> ( AAMT\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT. Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.\r\n<blockquote class=\"no-border text-center\">\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">Need an appointment?<\/p>\r\n<a class=\"theme_button color2\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact us<\/a><\/blockquote>\r\n<\/div>","post_title":"THOMAS STANISLAWSKI","post_excerpt":"Dr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance.","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"thomas-stanislawski","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-01 23:08:55","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 20:08:55","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"0","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/?post_type=team_member&#038;p=1870","menu_order":"0","post_type":"team_member","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2024","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-07 19:17:14","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-07 19:17:14","post_content":"<h2>Manual Therapy<\/h2>\r\nManual Therapy is among the oldest recorded influential interventions in medicine. Documentation of its practice dates back over 4,000 years to Egyptian scrolls. There is ample evidence of its usage in ancient China, India and Greece. While nobody questions these early origins of Manual Therapy, it is from the 19th century onwards that Manual Therapy has become an area of contention between the various professions involved in its practice - medicine, osteopathy, chiropractic and physical therapy.\r\n\r\n<b>Manual Therapy is a combination of art and science.<\/b>\r\n\r\nSuccessful application of Manual Therapy is dependent on the masterfully developed set of psychomotor skills (art component) and a solid, research evidence based foundation (science component).\r\n\r\n<b>Three notable forms of Manual Therapy are manipulation, mobilization and massage.<\/b>\r\n\r\nManipulation (also known as adjustment, or grade 5 mobilization, or mobilization with impulse or high velocity low amplitude thrust \u2013 HVLAT) is the artful application of a rapid force into a joint and tissues surrounding the joint. Manipulation is often associated with an audible popping sound. Manipulation techniques are difficult to master, they require a superb motor control being potentially the most dangerous ones. They are the most effective and clinically superior techniques for a number of orthopaedic conditions. These techniques are often credited with immediate improvement and complete elimination of pain and disability.\r\n\r\nMobilization (often incorrectly portrayed as a poor cousin of manipulation) is the artful application of a slower, more controlled force of varying amplitudes into a joint or soft-tissue surrounding the joint for a therapeutic purpose. Mobilization does not compete with manipulation, but has a well-defined place in Manual Therapy. Mobilization techniques are the very most difficult to master and they are indispensable, irreplaceable and most effective for certain orthopaedic conditions that HVLAT does not address.\r\n\r\nMassage is the artful application of a number of techniques consisting typically of the repetitive rubbing, stripping, compressing, stretching and kneading of myofascial tissues to principally improve interstitial fluid dynamics, improve mobility and relieve spasm and pain. Massage has a solid scientific and historical base and is the safest form of Manual Therapy.\r\n\r\n<h2>Osteopractic<\/h2>\r\nOsteopractic is a subspecialty open to PT, DO and MD practitioners. It is taught as a postgraduate program culminating in the Diploma in Osteopractic. Its core is Spinal Manipulative Therapy. Other parts include Dry Needling, extremity manipulation, usage of instruments and tools to treat soft tissue pathology and differential diagnosis. The program has a very strong, evidence based component.","post_title":"Manual Osteopractic","post_excerpt":"Shank corned beef boudin, hamburger pig cupim ground round landjaeger. Spare ribs pork frankfurter drumstick sirloin cupim salami. Ground round t-bone tail shank jerky, strip steak flank ribeye pancetta turducken salami cupim shoulder turkey swine. Short ribs meatloaf corned beef pastrami, tail pork belly alcatra filet mignon hamburger shoulder. Boudin short ribs pastrami, ham hock&hellip;","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"manual-osteopractic","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-02 00:47:22","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 21:47:22","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"0","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/?post_type=fw-services&#038;p=2024","menu_order":"0","post_type":"fw-services","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2026","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-07 19:18:47","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-07 19:18:47","post_content":"<h2>What is Physical Therapy?<\/h2>\r\nPhysical therapy (or physiotherapy) seeks to relieve pain, restore, maintain and promote optimal physical function as well as limit disabilities resulting from injury or disease.\r\n\r\nPhysical therapy utilizes a number of therapeutic methods, such as exercise therapy, manual therapy, electrotherapy also known as electrical physical agents (EPAs) such as laser, ultrasound, magnetic therapy, electrical stimulation as well as thermal agents of heat and cold. These agents are oftentimes referred to as modalities.\r\n<h3>Physical Therapists<\/h3>\r\nThe Doctor of Physical Therapy (DPT) degree is entry-level and the only PT degree offered by schools in the United States. Graduates have an option to go into a residency and then a fellowship.\r\n\r\nAs doctoral level direct access clinicians, we conduct an examination process that includes: taking your history, conducting a systems review, and performing tests and measures to identify the problem.\r\n\r\nWe will refer you to a different medical specialist if we determine that the problems to be addressed warrant such a referral.\r\n\r\nIf the problem falls within our scope, we establish a diagnosis (we tell you what the problem is) and a prognosis (we tell you how long it will take to resolve it).\r\n<h3>Treatment<\/h3>\r\nA comprehensive, tailored treatment plan is then created with a focus on your individual goals. Your therapist will utilize a range of treatment techniques to help you reach your goals.\r\n<h3>Rehabilitation<\/h3>\r\nRehabilitation is a process which is dedicated to restoring, improving and maintaining physical strength and mobility, cognition and overall wellness. Rehabilitation involves specialists from many disciplines. We collaborate and communicate with many trusted and dedicated professionals in the area and we share a common goal of helping you achieve the highest level of function, independence, and quality of life possible.\r\n<blockquote class=\"no-border text-center\">\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">Need an appointment?<\/p>\r\n<a class=\"fw-btn fw-btn-1 color2\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact us<\/a><\/blockquote>","post_title":"Physical Rehabilitation","post_excerpt":"Shank corned beef boudin, hamburger pig cupim ground round landjaeger. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2067","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-12 13:55:07","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-12 13:55:07","post_content":"<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2068 alignright\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_5481712_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_5481712_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>Stretching safely exposes your body to the strenuous limits that your sport or activity may introduce. By stretching in advance, it \u201cprepares\u201d the body for meeting those limits as they occur by loosening up the muscles slowly and carefully. Without stretching, if your muscle is forced to endure certain limits (typically very quickly and strongly), it can cause damage to the muscles. Stretching in advance will reduce the risk of injury because the muscle is already \u201cprepared\u201d for that exertion of force.\r\n<h2><strong>Increases Blood Flow for Performance<\/strong><\/h2>\r\nNot only does stretching improve flexibility and reduce the risk of injury, it will also help to improve the flow of blood through your body and the stretched muscles. Improved blood flow can help to improve overall performance, because each muscle is receiving more blood to help it perform more effectively.\r\n<strong>Quick Tips for Stretching<\/strong>\r\nStretching doesn\u2019t need to be complicated, but it should be worked into your exercising routine or before\/after any physical activities.<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2070 alignleft\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_30670855_original-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_30670855_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" \/>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Stretch major muscle groups, especially the areas you expect to use during your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Hold the stretch for a period of time (e.g., 30-60 seconds).<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Breathe normally during your stretching sessions.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Aim for tension, but not for pain during your stretches.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Keep movements smooth and avoid bouncing.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Tailor your stretches for your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nStay consistent with your stretching habits (e.g., a few times per week).\r\nWe\u2019ve launched our new Spanish website! When visiting<a href=\"http:\/\/www.nchs-salud.org\/\">\u00a0<\/a> you will have access to read NCHS content entirely in Spanish. On the new website, you will be able to view our health center locations, hours of operation, meet our providers, and many additional features without the need for translating! cares about the needs of our communities, and creating a website in Spanish aims to provide valuable information in a way that is most convenient for you. This website is another way, we\u2019re here for you!","post_title":"Reduces the Risk of Injury","post_excerpt":"Stretching safely exposes your body to the strenuous limits that your sport or activity may introduce. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2074","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-12 14:00:32","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-12 14:00:32","post_content":"With summer in full swing, everyone is out exploring, adventuring, and being active in their daily life. However, stretching after their physical activity is often overlooked. Many people forget about stretching, even those that are normally considered \u201cactive\u201d individuals. Developing good stretching habits can help to improve flexibility and performance, especially in sports and other physical activities.\r\n\r\n<strong>Greatly Improves Flexibility<\/strong>\r\n\r\nConsistent stretch habits can improve an individual\u2019s overall flexibility over time. This allows them to perform more efficiently during their sport or other physically demanding activity. Flexibility is important because it increase the range at which you can move each limb, allowing you to twist and reach further than you could without stretching.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reduces the Risk of Injury<\/strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2081 alignright\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_78288658_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_78288658_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>Stretching safely exposes your body to the strenuous limits that your sport or activity may introduce. By stretching in advance, it \u201cprepares\u201d the body for meeting those limits as they occur by loosening up the muscles slowly and carefully. Without stretching, if your muscle is forced to endure certain limits (typically very quickly and strongly), it can cause damage to the muscles. Stretching in advance will reduce the risk of injury because the muscle is already \u201cprepared\u201d for that exertion of force.\r\n\r\n<strong>Increases Blood Flow for Performance<\/strong>\r\n\r\nNot only does stretching improve flexibility and reduce the risk of injury, it will also help to improve the flow of blood through your body and the stretched muscles. Improved blood flow can help to improve overall performance, because each muscle is receiving more blood to help it perform more effectively.\r\n\r\n<strong>Quick Tips for Stretching<\/strong>\r\n\r\nStretching doesn\u2019t need to be complicated, but it should be worked into your exercising routine or before\/after any physical activities.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2080 alignleft\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_76571291_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_76571291_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>\r\n<ol>\r\n \t<li>Stretch major muscle groups, especially the areas you expect to use during your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Hold the stretch for a period of time (e.g., 30-60 seconds).<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Breathe normally during your stretching sessions.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Aim for tension, but not for pain during your stretches.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Keep movements smooth and avoid bouncing.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Tailor your stretches for your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Stay consistent with your stretching habits (e.g., a few times per week).<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<blockquote>Not only does stretching improve flexibility and reduce the risk of injury, it will also help to improve the flow of blood through your body and the stretched muscles. Improved blood flow can help to improve overall performance, because each muscle is receiving more blood to help it perform more effectively.<\/blockquote>","post_title":"Greatly Improves Flexibility","post_excerpt":"With summer in full swing, everyone is out exploring, adventuring, and being active in their daily life. However, stretching after their physical activity is often overlooked. Many people forget about stretching, even those that are normally considered \u201cactive\u201d individuals. Developing good stretching habits can help to improve flexibility and performance, especially in sports and other&hellip;","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","post_password":"","post_name":"greatly-improves-flexibility","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2016-09-15 08:29:32","post_modified_gmt":"2016-09-15 08:29:32","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"0","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/?p=2074","menu_order":"0","post_type":"post","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2093","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-13 07:54:30","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-13 07:54:30","post_content":"It\u2019s not uncommon for children who have obesity to become overweight adults. Teaching children healthy habits earlier encourages them to carry these healthy habits into adulthood. Not only will the child be healthier, but they\u2019ll learn the importance of proper discipline and healthy habits when it comes to food and exercise.\r\n\r\n<strong>Monitor the Activities That Promote Obesity<\/strong>\r\n\r\nAs a parent we should always be keeping an eye on what our children are up to. Obesity can affect anyone, even if other age groups or demographics may be at larger risk. This is why it\u2019s very important to monitor the types of activities that children are engaged in. While childhood obesity is a result of many different variables and factors, one of the largest contributors is taking part in an excessive amount of sedentary activities. Such activities include watching television, playing games on the computer, browsing the internet, watching videos online, and similar activities. While these are not inherently problematic, they can become a problem when done excessively.\r\n\r\n<strong>Develop Proper Sleep Habits and Routines<\/strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2068 alignleft\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_5481712_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_5481712_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>Lack of sleep can result in the body\u2019s inability to properly metabolize food efficiently. Without sleep, our bodies become less effective across the board and this can affect our weight in negative ways. This is why it\u2019s important to get children into proper sleep habits with regular bedtime routines that help them to maintain these habits without having to think about it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Find Places to Stay Active<\/strong>\r\n\r\nAlthough it\u2019s important to limit sedentary activities in excess (like watching TV or playing on the computer), it\u2019s sometimes not enough to counteract obesity in children. Children need to stay active and physically engaged through sports, exercise or other activities that keep them moving. While sports are not a requirement, finding ways for them to stay active is a great way to keep obesity away. Hiking and other family activities are a great way to get the entire family moving! are a few tips to motivate your kids to be more active.\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients\u00a0<\/strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>For Oats:<\/strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-2081\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_78288658_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_78288658_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/><\/strong>Wet\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>1\/4 cup apple sauce<\/li>\r\n \t<li>\u00bc cup nonfat Greek yogurt, plain<\/li>\r\n \t<li>\u00be cup almond milk, unsweetened<\/li>\r\n \t<li><\/li>\r\n \t<li><strong>For\u00a0Topping:<\/strong><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>1 apple<\/li>\r\n \t<li>1\/2 teaspoon coconut oil<\/li>\r\n \t<li>1\/2 tablespoon coconut sugar<\/li>\r\n \t<li>1\/2 teaspoon cinnamon<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<strong>Instructions for Oats:<\/strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n \t<li>First, mash 1\/2 banana in a large bowl. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2095","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-13 07:59:53","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-13 07:59:53","post_content":"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=cWQ14x1URXo\r\n\r\nWith summer in full swing, everyone is out exploring, adventuring, and being active in their daily life. However, stretching after their physical activity is often overlooked. Many people forget about stretching, even those that are normally considered \u201cactive\u201d individuals. Developing good stretching habits can help to improve flexibility and performance, especially in sports and other physical activities.\r\n\r\n<strong>Greatly Improves Flexibility<\/strong>\r\n\r\nConsistent stretch habits can improve an individual\u2019s overall flexibility over time. This allows them to perform more efficiently during their sport or other physically demanding activity. Flexibility is important because it increase the range at which you can move each limb, allowing you to twist and reach further than you could without stretching.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reduces the Risk of Injury<\/strong>\r\n\r\nStretching safely exposes your body to the strenuous limits that your sport or activity may introduce. By stretching in advance, it \u201cprepares\u201d the body for meeting those limits as they occur by loosening up the muscles slowly and carefully. Without stretching, if your muscle is forced to endure certain limits (typically very quickly and strongly), it can cause damage to the muscles. Stretching in advance will reduce the risk of injury because the muscle is already \u201cprepared\u201d for that exertion of force.\r\n\r\n<strong>Increases Blood Flow for Performance<\/strong>\r\n\r\nNot only does stretching improve flexibility and reduce the risk of injury, it will also help to improve the flow of blood through your body and the stretched muscles. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2099","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-13 08:04:00","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-13 08:04:00","post_content":"It\u2019s not uncommon for children who have obesity to become overweight adults. Teaching children healthy habits earlier encourages them to carry these healthy habits into adulthood. Not only will the child be healthier, but they\u2019ll learn the importance of proper discipline and healthy habits when it comes to food and exercise.\r\n\r\n<strong>Monitor the Activities That Promote Obesity<\/strong>\r\n<blockquote>As a parent we should always be keeping an eye on what our children are up to.<\/blockquote>\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2081 alignleft\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_78288658_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_78288658_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>Obesity can affect anyone, even if other age groups or demographics may be at larger risk. This is why it\u2019s very important to monitor the types of activities that children are engaged in. While childhood obesity is a result of many different variables and factors, one of the largest contributors is taking part in an excessive amount of sedentary activities. Such activities include watching television, playing games on the computer, browsing the internet, watching videos online, and similar activities. While these are not inherently problematic, they can become a problem when done excessively.\r\n\r\n<strong>Develop Proper Sleep Habits and Routines<\/strong>\r\n\r\nLack of sleep can result in the body\u2019s inability to properly metabolize food efficiently. Without sleep, our bodies become less effective across the board and this can affect our weight in negative ways. This is why it\u2019s important to get children into proper sleep habits with regular bedtime routines that help them to maintain these habits without having to think about it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Find Places to Stay Active<\/strong>\r\n\r\nAlthough it\u2019s important to limit sedentary activities in excess (like watching TV or playing on the computer), it\u2019s sometimes not enough to counteract obesity in children. Children need to stay active and physically engaged through sports, exercise or other activities that keep them moving. While sports are not a requirement, finding ways for them to stay active is a great way to keep obesity away. Hiking and other family activities are a great way to get the entire family moving! are a few tips to motivate your kids to be more active.\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 <\/strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>For Oats:<\/strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-2090\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_100740892_original-300x193.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_100740892_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"193\" \/><\/strong>Wet\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>1\/4 cup apple sauce<\/li>\r\n \t<li>\u00bc cup nonfat Greek yogurt, plain<\/li>\r\n \t<li>\u00be cup almond milk, unsweetened<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<strong>For\u00a0Topping:<\/strong>\r\n\r\n1 apple\r\n\r\n1\/2 teaspoon coconut oil\r\n\r\n1\/2 tablespoon coconut sugar\r\n\r\n1\/2 teaspoon cinnamon\r\n\r\n<strong>Instructions for Oats:<\/strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n \t<li>First, mash 1\/2 banana in a large bowl. Then add the rest of the wet ingredients in the mix until smooth.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Add in dry ingredients and mix again.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Place in the refrigerator, \u00a0covered, for at least 2 hours or overnight. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2103","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-13 08:13:54","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-13 08:13:54","post_content":"https:\/\/soundcloud.com\/aster-dm-healthcare\/aster-medical-centre-jlt\r\n\r\nWith summer in full swing, everyone is out exploring, adventuring, and being active in their daily life. However, stretching after their physical activity is often overlooked. Many people forget about stretching, even those that are normally considered \u201cactive\u201d individuals. Developing good stretching habits can help to improve flexibility and performance, especially in sports and other physical activities.\r\n\r\n<strong>Greatly Improves Flexibility<\/strong>\r\n\r\nConsistent stretch habits can improve an individual\u2019s overall flexibility over time. This allows them to perform more efficiently during their sport or other physically demanding activity. Flexibility is important because it increase the range at which you can move each limb, allowing you to twist and reach further than you could without stretching.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reduces the Risk of Injury<\/strong>\r\n\r\nStretching safely exposes your body to the strenuous limits that your sport or activity may introduce. By stretching in advance, it \u201cprepares\u201d the body for meeting those limits as they occur by loosening up the muscles slowly and carefully. Without stretching, if your muscle is forced to endure certain limits (typically very quickly and strongly), it can cause damage to the muscles. Stretching in advance will reduce the risk of injury because the muscle is already \u201cprepared\u201d for that exertion of force.\r\n\r\n<strong>Increases Blood Flow for Performance<\/strong>\r\n\r\nNot only does stretching improve flexibility and reduce the risk of injury, it will also help to improve the flow of blood through your body and the stretched muscles. Improved blood flow can help to improve overall performance, because each muscle is receiving more blood to help it perform more effectively.\r\n\r\n<strong>Quick Tips for Stretching<\/strong>\r\n\r\nStretching doesn\u2019t need to be complicated, but it should be worked into your exercising routine or before\/after any physical activities.\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-2087\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_83197200_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_83197200_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>Stretch major muscle groups, especially the areas you expect to use during your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Hold the stretch for a period of time (e.g., 30-60 seconds).<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Breathe normally during your stretching sessions.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Aim for tension, but not for pain during your stretches.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Keep movements smooth and avoid bouncing.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Tailor your stretches for your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Stay consistent with your stretching habits (e.g., a few times per week).<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Try these tips out and incorporate stretching into your daily life \u2013 in addition to your sports and physical activities!<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>","post_title":"Reduces the Risk of Injury","post_excerpt":"https:\/\/soundcloud.com\/aster-dm-healthcare\/aster-medical-centre-jlt With summer in full swing, everyone is out exploring, adventuring, and being active in their daily life. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2114","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-13 08:24:38","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-13 08:24:38","post_content":"It\u2019s not uncommon for children who have obesity to become overweight adults. Teaching children healthy habits earlier encourages them to carry these healthy habits into adulthood. Not only will the child be healthier, but they\u2019ll learn the importance of proper discipline and healthy habits when it comes to food and exercise.\r\n\r\n<strong>Monitor the Activities That Promote Obesity<\/strong>\r\n\r\nAs a parent we should always be keeping an eye on what our children are up to. Obesity can affect anyone, even if other age groups or demographics may be at larger risk. This is why it\u2019s very important to monitor the types of activities that children are engaged in. While childhood obesity is a result of many different variables and factors, one of the largest contributors is taking part in an excessive amount of sedentary activities. Such activities include watching television, playing games on the computer, browsing the internet, watching videos online, and similar activities. While these are not inherently problematic, they can become a problem when done excessively.\r\n\r\n<strong>Develop Proper Sleep Habits and Routines<\/strong>\r\n\r\nLack of sleep can result in the body\u2019s inability to properly metabolize food efficiently. Without sleep, our bodies become less effective across the board and this can affect our weight in negative ways. This is why it\u2019s important to get children into proper sleep habits with regular bedtime routines that help them to maintain these habits without having to think about it.\r\n\r\n[gallery ids=\"2091,2090,2089\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Find Places to Stay Active<\/strong>\r\n\r\nAlthough it\u2019s important to limit sedentary activities in excess (like watching TV or playing on the computer), it\u2019s sometimes not enough to counteract obesity in children. Children need to stay active and physically engaged through sports, exercise or other activities that keep them moving. While sports are not a requirement, finding ways for them to stay active is a great way to keep obesity away. Hiking and other family activities are a great way to get the entire family moving! are a few tips to motivate your kids to be more active.\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 <\/strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>For Oats:<\/strong>\r\n\r\nWet\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>1\/4 cup apple sauce<\/li>\r\n \t<li>\u00bc cup nonfat Greek yogurt, plain<\/li>\r\n \t<li>\u00be cup almond milk, unsweetened<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nIt\u2019s not uncommon for children who have obesity to become overweight adults. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2121","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-13 08:30:46","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-13 08:30:46","post_content":"<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2068 alignright\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_5481712_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_5481712_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>Stretching safely exposes your body to the strenuous limits that your sport or activity may introduce. By stretching in advance, it \u201cprepares\u201d the body for meeting those limits as they occur by loosening up the muscles slowly and carefully. Without stretching, if your muscle is forced to endure certain limits (typically very quickly and strongly), it can cause damage to the muscles. Stretching in advance will reduce the risk of injury because the muscle is already \u201cprepared\u201d for that exertion of force.\r\n<h2><strong>Increases Blood Flow for Performance<\/strong><\/h2>\r\nNot only does stretching improve flexibility and reduce the risk of injury, it will also help to improve the flow of blood through your body and the stretched muscles. Improved blood flow can help to improve overall performance, because each muscle is receiving more blood to help it perform more effectively.\r\n<strong>Quick Tips for Stretching<\/strong>\r\nStretching doesn\u2019t need to be complicated, but it should be worked into your exercising routine or before\/after any physical activities.\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Stretch major muscle groups, especially the areas you expect to use during your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Hold the stretch for a period of time (e.g., 30-60 seconds).<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Breathe normally during your stretching sessions.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Aim for tension, but not for pain during your stretches.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Keep movements smooth and avoid bouncing.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Tailor your stretches for your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nStay consistent with your stretching habits (e.g., a few times per week).\r\nWe\u2019ve launched our new Spanish website! This website is another way, we\u2019re here for you!\r\n\r\nAs a parent we should always be keeping an eye on what our children are up to. Obesity can affect anyone, even if other age groups or demographics may be at larger risk. This is why it\u2019s very important to monitor the types of activities that children are engaged in. While childhood obesity is a result of many different variables and factors, one of the largest contributors is taking part in an excessive amount of sedentary activities. Such activities include watching television, playing games on the computer, browsing the internet, watching videos online, and similar activities. While these are not inherently problematic, they can become a problem when done excessively.\r\n\r\n<strong>Develop Proper Sleep Habits and Routines<\/strong>\r\n\r\nLack of sleep can result in the body\u2019s inability to properly metabolize food efficiently. Without sleep, our bodies become less effective across the board and this can affect our weight in negative ways. This is why it\u2019s important to get children into proper sleep habits with regular bedtime routines that help them to maintain these habits without having to think about it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Find Places to Stay Active<\/strong>\r\n\r\nAlthough it\u2019s important to limit sedentary activities in excess (like watching TV or playing on the computer), it\u2019s sometimes not enough to counteract obesity in children. Children need to stay active and physically engaged through sports, exercise or other activities that keep them moving. While sports are not a requirement, finding ways for them to stay active is a great way to keep obesity away. Hiking and other family activities are a great way to get the entire family moving! are a few tips to motivate your kids to be more active.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2070 alignleft\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_30670855_original-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_30670855_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" \/><strong>Ingredients\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 <\/strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>For Oats:<\/strong>\r\n\r\nWet\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>1\/4 cup apple sauce<\/li>\r\n \t<li>\u00bc cup nonfat Greek yogurt, plain<\/li>\r\n \t<li>\u00be cup almond milk, unsweetened<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nDry\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>1 cup rolled oats<\/li>\r\n \t<li>1\/2 teaspoon cinnamon<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<strong>For\u00a0Topping:<\/strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>1 apple<\/li>\r\n \t<li>1\/2 teaspoon coconut oil<\/li>\r\n \t<li>1\/2 tablespoon coconut sugar<\/li>\r\n \t<li>1\/2 teaspoon cinnamon<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<strong>Instructions for Oats:<\/strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n \t<li>First, mash 1\/2 banana in a large bowl. By stretching in advance, it \u201cprepares\u201d the body for meeting those limits as they occur by loosening up the muscles slowly and carefully. Without stretching, if your muscle is forced to endure certain limits (typically very quickly and strongly), it can cause damage to the muscles. Stretching in advance will reduce the risk of injury because the muscle is already \u201cprepared\u201d for that exertion of force.\r\n<h2><strong>Increases Blood Flow for Performance<\/strong><\/h2>\r\nNot only does stretching improve flexibility and reduce the risk of injury, it will also help to improve the flow of blood through your body and the stretched muscles. Improved blood flow can help to improve overall performance, because each muscle is receiving more blood to help it perform more effectively.\r\n<strong>Quick Tips for Stretching<\/strong>\r\nStretching doesn\u2019t need to be complicated, but it should be worked into your exercising routine or before\/after any physical activities.<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2070 alignright\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_30670855_original-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_30670855_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" \/>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Stretch major muscle groups, especially the areas you expect to use during your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Hold the stretch for a period of time (e.g., 30-60 seconds).<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Breathe normally during your stretching sessions.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Aim for tension, but not for pain during your stretches.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Keep movements smooth and avoid bouncing.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Tailor your stretches for your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nStay consistent with your stretching habits (e.g., a few times per week).\r\nWe\u2019ve launched our new Spanish website! When visiting<a href=\"http:\/\/www.nchs-salud.org\/\">\u00a0<\/a> you will have access to read NCHS content entirely in Spanish. On the new website, you will be able to view our health center locations, hours of operation, meet our providers, and many additional features without the need for translating! cares about the needs of our communities, and creating a website in Spanish aims to provide valuable information in a way that is most convenient for you. This website is another way, we\u2019re here for you!\r\n\r\n<strong>Reduces the Risk of Injury<\/strong>\r\n\r\nStretching safely exposes your body to the strenuous limits that your sport or activity may introduce. By stretching in advance, it \u201cprepares\u201d the body for meeting those limits as they occur by loosening up the muscles slowly and carefully. Without stretching, if your muscle is forced to endure certain limits (typically very quickly and strongly), it can cause damage to the muscles. Stretching in advance will reduce the risk of injury because the muscle is already \u201cprepared\u201d for that exertion of force.","post_title":"Blood Flow","post_excerpt":"Stretching safely exposes your body to the strenuous limits that your sport or activity may introduce. By stretching in advance, it \u201cprepares\u201d the body for meeting those limits as they occur by loosening up the muscles slowly and carefully. Without stretching, if your muscle is forced to endure certain limits (typically very quickly and strongly),&hellip;","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","post_password":"","post_name":"blood-flow","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2016-09-15 08:33:01","post_modified_gmt":"2016-09-15 08:33:01","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"0","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/?p=2167","menu_order":"0","post_type":"post","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

While childhood obesity is a result of many different variables and factors, one of the largest contributors is taking part in an excessive amount of sedentary activities. Such activities include watching television, playing games on the computer, browsing the internet, watching videos online, and similar activities. While these are not inherently problematic, they can become a problem when done excessively.\r\n\r\n<strong>Develop Proper Sleep Habits and Routines<\/strong>\r\n\r\nLack of sleep can result in the body\u2019s inability to properly metabolize food efficiently. Without stretching, if your muscle is forced to endure certain limits (typically very quickly and strongly), it can cause damage to the muscles. Stretching in advance will reduce the risk of injury because the muscle is already \u201cprepared\u201d for that exertion of force.\r\n<h2><strong>Increases Blood Flow for Performance<\/strong><\/h2>\r\nNot only does stretching improve flexibility and reduce the risk of injury, it will also help to improve the flow of blood through your body and the stretched muscles. Improved blood flow can help to improve overall performance, because each muscle is receiving more blood to help it perform more effectively.\r\n<strong>Quick Tips for Stretching<\/strong>\r\nStretching doesn\u2019t need to be complicated, but it should be worked into your exercising routine or before\/after any physical activities.<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2070 alignleft\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_30670855_original-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_30670855_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" \/>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Stretch major muscle groups, especially the areas you expect to use during your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Hold the stretch for a period of time (e.g., 30-60 seconds).<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Breathe normally during your stretching sessions.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Aim for tension, but not for pain during your stretches.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Keep movements smooth and avoid bouncing.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Tailor your stretches for your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nStay consistent with your stretching habits (e.g., a few times per week).\r\nWe\u2019ve launched our new Spanish website! When visiting<a href=\"http:\/\/www.nchs-salud.org\/\">\u00a0<\/a> you will have access to read NCHS content entirely in Spanish. On the new website, you will be able to view our health center locations, hours of operation, meet our providers, and many additional features without the need for translating! cares about the needs of our communities, and creating a website in Spanish aims to provide valuable information in a way that is most convenient for you. This website is another way, we\u2019re here for you!","post_title":"Stretching","post_excerpt":"Stretching safely exposes your body to the strenuous limits that your sport or activity may introduce. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2200","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-13 10:12:42","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-13 10:12:42","post_content":"<strong>The Earlier You Start, the Better<\/strong>\r\n\r\nIt\u2019s not uncommon for children who have obesity to become overweight adults. Teaching children healthy habits earlier encourages them to carry these healthy habits into adulthood. Not only will the child be healthier, but they\u2019ll learn the importance of proper discipline and healthy habits when it comes to food and exercise.\r\n<blockquote>As a parent we should always be keeping an eye on what our children are up to.<\/blockquote>\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-2082\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_78288682_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_78288682_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>Obesity can affect anyone, even if other age groups or demographics may be at larger risk. This is why it\u2019s very important to monitor the types of activities that children are engaged in. While childhood obesity is a result of many different variables and factors, one of the largest contributors is taking part in an excessive amount of sedentary activities. Such activities include watching television, playing games on the computer, browsing the internet, watching videos online, and similar activities. While these are not inherently problematic, they can become a problem when done excessively.\r\n\r\n<strong>Develop Proper Sleep Habits and Routines<\/strong>\r\n\r\nLack of sleep can result in the body\u2019s inability to properly metabolize food efficiently. Without sleep, our bodies become less effective across the board and this can affect our weight in negative ways. This is why it\u2019s important to get children into proper sleep habits with regular bedtime routines that help them to maintain these habits without having to think about it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Find Places to Stay Active<\/strong>\r\n\r\nAlthough it\u2019s important to limit sedentary activities in excess (like watching TV or playing on the computer), it\u2019s sometimes not enough to counteract obesity in children. Children need to stay active and physically engaged through sports, exercise or other activities that keep them moving. While sports are not a requirement, finding ways for them to stay active is a great way to keep obesity away. Hiking and other family activities are a great way to get the entire family moving! are a few tips to motivate your kids to be more active.\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 <\/strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>For Oats:<\/strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-2090\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_100740892_original-300x193.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_100740892_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"193\" \/><\/strong>Wet\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>1\/4 cup apple sauce<\/li>\r\n \t<li>\u00bc cup nonfat Greek yogurt, plain<\/li>\r\n \t<li>\u00be cup almond milk, unsweetened<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<strong>Instructions for Oats:<\/strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n \t<li>First, mash 1\/2 banana in a large bowl. Then add the rest of the wet ingredients in the mix until smooth.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Add in dry ingredients and mix again.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Place in the refrigerator, \u00a0covered, for at least 2 hours or overnight. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2205","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-13 10:14:31","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-13 10:14:31","post_content":"With summer in full swing, everyone is out exploring, adventuring, and being active in their daily life. However, stretching after their physical activity is often overlooked. Many people forget about stretching, even those that are normally considered \u201cactive\u201d individuals. Developing good stretching habits can help to improve flexibility and performance, especially in sports and other physical activities.\r\n\r\n<strong>Greatly Improves Flexibility<\/strong>\r\n\r\nConsistent stretch habits can improve an individual\u2019s overall flexibility over time. This allows them to perform more efficiently during their sport or other physically demanding activity. By stretching in advance, it \u201cprepares\u201d the body for meeting those limits as they occur by loosening up the muscles slowly and carefully.
