{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2281","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-13 11:40:51","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-13 11:40:51","post_content":"<strong>The Earlier You Start, the Better<\/strong>\r\n\r\nIt\u2019s not uncommon for children who have obesity to become overweight adults. Teaching children healthy habits earlier encourages them to carry these healthy habits into adulthood. Not only will the child be healthier, but they\u2019ll learn the importance of proper discipline and healthy habits when it comes to food and exercise.\r\n<blockquote>As a parent we should always be keeping an eye on what our children are up to.<\/blockquote>\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-2082\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_78288682_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_78288682_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>Obesity can affect anyone, even if other age groups or demographics may be at larger risk. This is why it\u2019s very important to monitor the types of activities that children are engaged in. While childhood obesity is a result of many different variables and factors, one of the largest contributors is taking part in an excessive amount of sedentary activities. Such activities include watching television, playing games on the computer, browsing the internet, watching videos online, and similar activities. While these are not inherently problematic, they can become a problem when done excessively.\r\n\r\n<strong>Develop Proper Sleep Habits and Routines<\/strong>\r\n\r\nLack of sleep can result in the body\u2019s inability to properly metabolize food efficiently. Without sleep, our bodies become less effective across the board and this can affect our weight in negative ways. This is why it\u2019s important to get children into proper sleep habits with regular bedtime routines that help them to maintain these habits without having to think about it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Find Places to Stay Active<\/strong>\r\n\r\nAlthough it\u2019s important to limit sedentary activities in excess (like watching TV or playing on the computer), it\u2019s sometimes not enough to counteract obesity in children. Children need to stay active and physically engaged through sports, exercise or other activities that keep them moving. While sports are not a requirement, finding ways for them to stay active is a great way to keep obesity away. Hiking and other family activities are a great way to get the entire family moving! are a few tips to motivate your kids to be more active.\r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 <\/strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>For Oats:<\/strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-2090\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_100740892_original-300x193.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_100740892_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"193\" \/><\/strong>Wet\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>1\/4 cup apple sauce<\/li>\r\n \t<li>\u00bc cup nonfat Greek yogurt, plain<\/li>\r\n \t<li>\u00be cup almond milk, unsweetened<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<strong>Instructions for Oats:<\/strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n \t<li>First, mash 1\/2 banana in a large bowl. Then add the rest of the wet ingredients in the mix until smooth.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Add in dry ingredients and mix again.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Place in the refrigerator, \u00a0covered, for at least 2 hours or overnight. Serve cold.<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>","post_title":"Increases Blood","post_excerpt":"The Earlier You Start, the Better It\u2019s not uncommon for children who have obesity to become overweight adults. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2282","post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-09-13 11:39:43","post_date_gmt":"2016-09-13 11:39:43","post_content":"With summer in full swing, everyone is out exploring, adventuring, and being active in their daily life. However, stretching after their physical activity is often overlooked. Many people forget about stretching, even those that are normally considered \u201cactive\u201d individuals. Developing good stretching habits can help to improve flexibility and performance, especially in sports and other physical activities.\r\n\r\n<strong>Greatly Improves Flexibility<\/strong>\r\n\r\nConsistent stretch habits can improve an individual\u2019s overall flexibility over time. This allows them to perform more efficiently during their sport or other physically demanding activity. Flexibility is important because it increase the range at which you can move each limb, allowing you to twist and reach further than you could without stretching.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reduces the Risk of Injury<\/strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2081 alignright\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_78288658_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_78288658_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>Stretching safely exposes your body to the strenuous limits that your sport or activity may introduce. By stretching in advance, it \u201cprepares\u201d the body for meeting those limits as they occur by loosening up the muscles slowly and carefully. Without stretching, if your muscle is forced to endure certain limits (typically very quickly and strongly), it can cause damage to the muscles. Stretching in advance will reduce the risk of injury because the muscle is already \u201cprepared\u201d for that exertion of force.\r\n\r\n<strong>Increases Blood Flow for Performance<\/strong>\r\n\r\nNot only does stretching improve flexibility and reduce the risk of injury, it will also help to improve the flow of blood through your body and the stretched muscles. Improved blood flow can help to improve overall performance, because each muscle is receiving more blood to help it perform more effectively.\r\n\r\n<strong>Quick Tips for Stretching<\/strong>\r\n\r\nStretching doesn\u2019t need to be complicated, but it should be worked into your exercising routine or before\/after any physical activities.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2080 alignleft\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Depositphotos_76571291_original-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"depositphotos_76571291_original\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" \/>\r\n<ol>\r\n \t<li>Stretch major muscle groups, especially the areas you expect to use during your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Hold the stretch for a period of time (e.g., 30-60 seconds).<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Breathe normally during your stretching sessions.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Aim for tension, but not for pain during your stretches.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Keep movements smooth and avoid bouncing.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Tailor your stretches for your sport or activity.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Stay consistent with your stretching habits (e.g., a few times per week).<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<blockquote>Not only does stretching improve flexibility and reduce the risk of injury, it will also help to improve the flow of blood through your body and the stretched muscles. Improved blood flow can help to improve overall performance, because each muscle is receiving more blood to help it perform more effectively.<\/blockquote>","post_title":"Injury","post_excerpt":"With summer in full swing, everyone is out exploring, adventuring, and being active in their daily life. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2531","post_author":"1","post_date":"2017-12-29 01:20:14","post_date_gmt":"2017-12-28 22:20:14","post_content":"<h1>Treatment<\/h1><p>Headaches can be caused by multiple issues and may be direct or referred in nature. Direct headaches will have their origin within your head and may relate to stress, chemical changes within your brain, food reactions, or other causes. Headaches can often be referred from your cervical spine (neck), your mid to upper back and your jaw. Referred headaches can often relate to poor posture, or inadequate flexibility or stability around the neck.<\/p><p>Regardless of the potential issues at play, we specialize in thorough analysis and assessment. Our clinicians identify issues and develop treatment programs to deliver effective outcomes.<\/p><p>Common conditions :<\/p><p>The head and neck are complex interrelated structures comprising intricate networks of discs, ligaments, vessels and vertebrae. As a result, there can be multiple factors contributing to head or neck pain. Some of the more common conditions we treat include post-surgical rehabilitation, disc problems, stiffness, facet joint dysfunction, neck related headaches, postural problems, acute sprains and strains, osteoarthritis and arm pain referring from the neck.<\/p>\n\n<!-- 12e51e9b56fe7a9d0d0cc538160ed395 -->","post_title":"","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"trash","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"treatment__trashed","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-01 23:00:14","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 20:00:14","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"0","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/?page_id=2531","menu_order":"0","post_type":"page","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2553","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-01 19:46:02","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 16:46:02","post_content":"<img src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/03-e1514824230679-371x371.jpg\" alt=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/03-e1514824230679-371x371.jpg\" width=\"371\" height=\"371\" \/><h4>DR. THOMAS STANISLAWSKI<\/h4><p class=\"small-text\">FELLOWSHIP TRAINED IN OMT<\/p> \n <h2 class=\"section_header\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/h2><p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">DPT, FAAOMPT, Dip. Osteopractic Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p><p class=\"bottommargin_10\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance. Dr. Stanislawski\u2019s unique style is influenced by several OMT (Orthopaedic Manual\/Manipulative Therapy) systems he studied. This included but wasn't limited to:<\/p><p>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:\u00a0This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the American Academy of Manipulative Therapy\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\/ Dry Needling Institute. After multiple written, oral and practical examinations and earning Certification in Dry Needling (Cert. DN), Certification in Spinal Manipulative Therapy (Cert. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\/DO\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors.<\/p><p>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:\u00a0This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT). After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State.<\/p><p>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:\u00a0The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force. After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques.<\/p><p>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY\u00a0( AAMT\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT. Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.<\/p>\n\n<!-- 80ff12b5ec7818dbe4e189a8003c0934 -->","post_title":"","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"trash","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2553-2__trashed","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-01 23:00:14","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 20:00:14","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"0","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/?page_id=2553","menu_order":"0","post_type":"page","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2555","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-01 19:46:02","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 16:46:02","post_content":"<img src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/03-e1514824230679-371x371.jpg\" alt=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/03-e1514824230679-371x371.jpg\" width=\"371\" height=\"371\" \/><h4>DR. THOMAS STANISLAWSKI<\/h4><p class=\"small-text\">FELLOWSHIP TRAINED IN OMT<\/p> \n <h2 class=\"section_header\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/h2><p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">DPT, FAAOMPT, Dip. Osteopractic Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p><p class=\"bottommargin_10\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance. Dr. Stanislawski\u2019s unique style is influenced by several OMT (Orthopaedic Manual\/Manipulative Therapy) systems he studied. This included but wasn't limited to:<\/p><p>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:\u00a0This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the American Academy of Manipulative Therapy\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\/ Dry Needling Institute. After multiple written, oral and practical examinations and earning Certification in Dry Needling (Cert. DN), Certification in Spinal Manipulative Therapy (Cert. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\/DO\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors.<\/p><p>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:\u00a0This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT). After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State.<\/p><p>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:\u00a0The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force. After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques.<\/p><p>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY\u00a0( AAMT\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT. Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.<\/p>\n\n<!-- 80ff12b5ec7818dbe4e189a8003c0934 -->","post_title":"","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"inherit","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2553-revision-v1","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-01 19:46:02","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 16:46:02","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"2553","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/2018\/01\/01\/2553-revision-v1\/","menu_order":"0","post_type":"revision","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

Osteopractic Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n<p class=\"bottommargin_10\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance. Dr. Stanislawski\u2019s unique style is influenced by several OMT (Orthopaedic Manual\/Manipulative Therapy) systems he studied. This included but wasn't limited to:<\/p>\r\n<b>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:<\/b> This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the American Academy of Manipulative Therapy\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\/ Dry Needling Institute. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\/DO\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors.\r\n\r\n<!-- Nav tabs -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Tab panes -->\r\n\r\n<b>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:<\/b> This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT). After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State.\r\n\r\n<b>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:<\/b> The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force. After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques.\r\n\r\n<b>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY<\/b> ( AAMT\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT. Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.\r\n<blockquote class=\"no-border text-center\">\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">Need an appointment?<\/p>\r\n<a class=\"theme_button color2\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact us<\/a><\/blockquote>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/section>","post_title":"","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"trash","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2556-2__trashed","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-01 23:00:15","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 20:00:15","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"0","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/?page_id=2556","menu_order":"0","post_type":"page","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2560","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-01 19:57:36","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 16:57:36","post_content":"<section class=\"ls page_portfolio section_padding_150\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-5\">\r\n<div class=\"thumbnail text-center\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"rounded\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/03-e1514824230679.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/>\r\n<div class=\"caption\">\r\n<h4><a href=\"team-single.html\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/a><\/h4>\r\n<p class=\"small-text\">Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"divider_15\" \/>\r\n<p class=\"social-icons greylinks margin_0\"><\/p>\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-7\">\r\n<h2 class=\"section_header\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/h2>\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">DPT, FAAOMPT, Dip. Osteopractic Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n<p class=\"bottommargin_10\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance. Dr. Stanislawski\u2019s unique style is influenced by several OMT (Orthopaedic Manual\/Manipulative Therapy) systems he studied. This included but wasn't limited to:<\/p>\r\n<b>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:<\/b> This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the American Academy of Manipulative Therapy\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\/ Dry Needling Institute. After multiple written, oral and practical examinations and earning Certification in Dry Needling (Cert. DN), Certification in Spinal Manipulative Therapy (Cert. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\/DO\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors.\r\n\r\n<!-- Nav tabs -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Tab panes -->\r\n\r\n<b>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:<\/b> This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT). After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State.\r\n\r\n<b>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:<\/b> The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force. After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques.\r\n\r\n<b>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY<\/b> ( AAMT\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT. Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.\r\n<blockquote class=\"no-border text-center\">\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">Need an appointment?<\/p>\r\n<a class=\"theme_button color2\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact us<\/a><\/blockquote>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/section>","post_title":"","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"inherit","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2556-revision-v1","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-01 19:57:36","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 16:57:36","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"2556","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/2018\/01\/01\/2556-revision-v1\/","menu_order":"0","post_type":"revision","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}
{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2561","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-01 19:59:01","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 16:59:01","post_content":"<section class=\"ls page_portfolio section_padding_150\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-5\">\r\n<div class=\" text-center\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"rounded\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/03-e1514824230679.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/>\r\n<div class=\"caption\">\r\n<h4><a href=\"team-single.html\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/a><\/h4>\r\n<p class=\"small-text\">Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"divider_15\" \/>\r\n<p class=\"social-icons greylinks margin_0\"><\/p>\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-7\">\r\n<h2 class=\"section_header\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/h2>\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">DPT, FAAOMPT, Dip. Osteopractic Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n<p class=\"bottommargin_10\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance. Dr. Stanislawski\u2019s unique style is influenced by several OMT (Orthopaedic Manual\/Manipulative Therapy) systems he studied. This included but wasn't limited to:<\/p>\r\n<b>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:<\/b> This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the American Academy of Manipulative Therapy\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\/ Dry Needling Institute. After multiple written, oral and practical examinations and earning Certification in Dry Needling (Cert. DN), Certification in Spinal Manipulative Therapy (Cert. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\/DO\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors.\r\n\r\n<!-- Nav tabs -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Tab panes -->\r\n\r\n<b>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:<\/b> This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT). After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State.\r\n\r\n<b>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:<\/b> The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force. After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques.\r\n\r\n<b>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY<\/b> ( AAMT\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT. Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.\r\n<blockquote class=\"no-border text-center\">\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">Need an appointment?<\/p>\r\n<a class=\"theme_button color2\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact us<\/a><\/blockquote>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/section>","post_title":"","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"inherit","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2556-revision-v1","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-01 19:59:01","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 16:59:01","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"2556","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/2018\/01\/01\/2556-revision-v1\/","menu_order":"0","post_type":"revision","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2576","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-01 23:04:40","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 20:04:40","post_content":"<div class=\"col-md-7\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"section_header\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/h2>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">DPT, FAAOMPT, Dip. Osteopractic                                                                                      Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"bottommargin_10\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tDr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance. Dr. Stanislawski\u2019s unique style is influenced by several OMT  (Orthopaedic Manual\/Manipulative Therapy) systems he studied.  This included but wasn't limited to:\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:<\/b>  This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the  American Academy of  Manipulative Therapy\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\/ Dry Needling Institute. After multiple written, oral and practical examinations and earning Certification in Dry Needling (Cert. DN), Certification in Spinal Manipulative Therapy (Cert. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic  and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\/DO\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors. \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/p>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Nav tabs -->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Tab panes -->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:<\/b> This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with  North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT).  After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State. \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/p>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:<\/b> The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force.   After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques. \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY<\/b> ( AAMT\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT.  Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.  \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/p>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<blockquote class=\"no-border text-center\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">Need an appointment?<\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"theme_button color2\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact us<\/a>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/blockquote>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>","post_title":"THOMAS STANISLAWSKI","post_excerpt":"Biography: Kevin shankle short ribs turducken chicken porchetta. {"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2577","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-01 23:05:44","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 20:05:44","post_content":"\r\n<h2 class=\"section_header\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/h2>\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">DPT, FAAOMPT, Dip. Osteopractic Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n<p class=\"bottommargin_10\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance. Dr. Stanislawski\u2019s unique style is influenced by several OMT (Orthopaedic Manual\/Manipulative Therapy) systems he studied. This included but wasn't limited to:<\/p>\r\n<b>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:<\/b> This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the American Academy of Manipulative Therapy\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\/ Dry Needling Institute. After multiple written, oral and practical examinations and earning Certification in Dry Needling (Cert. DN), Certification in Spinal Manipulative Therapy (Cert. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\/DO\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors.\r\n\r\n<!-- Nav tabs -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Tab panes -->\r\n\r\n<b>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:<\/b> This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT). After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State.\r\n\r\n<b>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:<\/b> The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force. After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques.\r\n\r\n<b>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY<\/b> ( AAMT\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT. Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.\r\n<blockquote class=\"no-border text-center\">\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">Need an appointment?<\/p>\r\n<a class=\"theme_button color2\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact us<\/a><\/blockquote>\r\n<\/div>","post_title":"THOMAS STANISLAWSKI","post_excerpt":"Biography: Kevin shankle short ribs turducken chicken porchetta. class=\"col-md-7\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"section_header\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/h2>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">DPT, FAAOMPT, Dip. Osteopractic                                                                                      Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"bottommargin_10\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tDr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance. Dr. Stanislawski\u2019s unique style is influenced by several OMT  (Orthopaedic Manual\/Manipulative Therapy) systems he studied.  This included but wasn't limited to:\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:<\/b>  This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the  American Academy of  Manipulative Therapy\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\/ Dry Needling Institute. After multiple written, oral and practical examinations and earning Certification in Dry Needling (Cert. DN), Certification in Spinal Manipulative Therapy (Cert. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic  and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\/DO\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors. \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/p>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Nav tabs -->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!-- Tab panes -->\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:<\/b> This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with  North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT).  After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State. \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/p>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:<\/b> The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force.   After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques. \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<b>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY<\/b> ( AAMT\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT.  Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.  \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/p>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<blockquote class=\"no-border text-center\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">Need an appointment?<\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"theme_button color2\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact us<\/a>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/blockquote>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\r\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\r\n\t\t\t<\/section>","post_title":"Dr. Thomas Stanislawski","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"inherit","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2579-revision-v1","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-01 23:12:27","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 20:12:27","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"2579","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/2018\/01\/01\/2579-revision-v1\/","menu_order":"0","post_type":"revision","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}
{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2581","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-01 23:12:49","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 20:12:49","post_content":"<section class=\"page_breadcrumbs ls ms ms2 section_padding_15 columns_margin_0\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 text-center\">\r\n<ol class=\"breadcrumb greylinks\">\r\n \t<li><a href=\"index.html\">\r\nHome\r\n<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li><a href=\"doctors.html\">Doctors<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li class=\"active\">Dr. Stanislawski<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/section><section class=\"ls page_portfolio section_padding_150\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-5\">\r\n<div class=\"thumbnail text-center\"><img class=\"rounded\" src=\"images\/team\/01.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/>\r\n<div class=\"caption\">\r\n<h4><a href=\"team-single.html\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/a><\/h4>\r\n<p class=\"small-text\">Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"divider_15\" \/>\r\n<p class=\"social-icons greylinks margin_0\"><\/p>\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-7\">\r\n<h2 class=\"section_header\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/h2>\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">DPT, FAAOMPT, Dip. Osteopractic Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n<p class=\"bottommargin_10\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance. Dr. Stanislawski\u2019s unique style is influenced by several OMT (Orthopaedic Manual\/Manipulative Therapy) systems he studied. This included but wasn't limited to:<\/p>\r\n<b>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:<\/b> This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the American Academy of Manipulative Therapy\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\/ Dry Needling Institute. After multiple written, oral and practical examinations and earning Certification in Dry Needling (Cert. DN), Certification in Spinal Manipulative Therapy (Cert. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\/DO\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors.\r\n\r\n<!-- Nav tabs -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Tab panes -->\r\n\r\n<b>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:<\/b> This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT). After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State.\r\n\r\n<b>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:<\/b> The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force. After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques.\r\n\r\n<b>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY<\/b> ( AAMT\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT. Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.\r\n<blockquote class=\"no-border text-center\">\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">Need an appointment?<\/p>\r\n<a class=\"theme_button color2\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact us<\/a><\/blockquote>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/section>","post_title":"Dr. Thomas Stanislawski","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"inherit","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2579-revision-v1","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-01 23:12:49","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 20:12:49","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"2579","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/2018\/01\/01\/2579-revision-v1\/","menu_order":"0","post_type":"revision","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques.\r\n\r\n<b>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY<\/b> ( AAMT\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT. Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.\r\n<blockquote class=\" text-center\">\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">Need an appointment?<\/p>\r\n<a class=\"theme_button color2\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact us<\/a><\/blockquote>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/section>","post_title":"Dr. Thomas Stanislawski","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"inherit","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2579-revision-v1","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-01 23:21:25","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 20:21:25","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"2579","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/2018\/01\/01\/2579-revision-v1\/","menu_order":"0","post_type":"revision","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2611","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-01 23:50:04","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 20:50:04","post_content":"<section class=\"ls page_portfolio section_padding_150\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-5\">\r\n<div class=\" text-center\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"rounded\" src=\"http:\/\/rehab\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/01.jpg\" alt=\"Dr. Thomas Stanislawski\" \/>\r\n<div class=\"caption\">\r\n<h4><a href=\"team-single.html\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/a><\/h4>\r\n<p class=\"small-text\">Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"divider_15\" \/>\r\n<p class=\"social-icons greylinks margin_0\"><\/p>\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-7\">\r\n<h2 class=\"section_header\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski<\/h2>\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">DPT, FAAOMPT, Dip. Osteopractic Fellowship Trained in OMT<\/p>\r\n<p class=\"bottommargin_10\">Dr. Thomas Stanislawski graduated from Long Island University, Brooklyn with a Doctorate degree in Physical Therapy where he also earned the Academic Excellence Award for his outstanding educational performance. Dr. Stanislawski\u2019s unique style is influenced by several OMT (Orthopaedic Manual\/Manipulative Therapy) systems he studied. This included but wasn't limited to:<\/p>\r\n<b>1) OSTEOPRACTIC SYSTEM:<\/b> This system is taught as a post-graduate, evidence based program conducted by the American Academy of Manipulative Therapy\/Spinal Manipulation Institute\/ Dry Needling Institute. After multiple written, oral and practical examinations and earning Certification in Dry Needling (Cert. DN), Certification in Spinal Manipulative Therapy (Cert. SMT), proving competent in the extremity thrust manipulation, usage of Instrument Assisted Soft Tissue Mobilization (IASTM) and meeting all other requirements of the Academy Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Diploma in Osteopractic and became the first Osteopractor in New York State. Diploma in Osteopractic is available only to MD\/DO\/PT practitioners. It is not available to chiropractors.\r\n\r\n<!-- Nav tabs -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Tab panes -->\r\n\r\n<b>2) NAIOMT SYSTEM:<\/b> This system draws extensively on the work of James Cyriax, MD and the OMT Nordic System and is taught as a comprehensive, post-graduate manual therapy series organized by Andrews University, MI in cooperation with North American Institute of Orthopaedic Manual Therapy (NAIOMT). After completing all levels and demonstrating through written and practical exams a level of safety and competency Dr. Stanislawski was awarded a Certificate of Competence in Spinal Corrective Thrust Technique becoming the first such practitioner in New York State.\r\n\r\n<b>3) MULLIGAN CONCEPT:<\/b> The Mulligan system of manual therapy is a complete system for treating the axial and appendicular joints using gentle mobilizing force. After completing all levels and demonstrating through written, oral and practical exams a level of safety and competency he was awarded a CMP - Certified Mulligan Practitioner title. The CMP title also attests to the proficiency in the usage of rigid tape and application of strapping techniques.\r\n\r\n<b>4) FELLOWSHIP in ORTHOPAEDIC MANUAL THERAPY<\/b> ( AAMT\/ University of South Carolina) - attainment of the Fellowship credential represents the highest level of proficiency and professionalism in OMT. Fellowship program develops and graduates practitioners, who by virtue of their critical thinking ability, clinical skills, diagnostic competence, and ethical standards are committed to promoting the optimum health and function of their patients, and who serve the profession through teaching, administration and research. Dr. Stanislawski mentors one Fellow-in-Training each year.\r\n<blockquote class=\" text-center\">\r\n<p class=\"yantramanov highlight\">Need an appointment?<\/p>\r\n<a class=\"fw-btn fw-btn-1\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact us<\/a><\/blockquote>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/section>","post_title":"Dr. Thomas Stanislawski","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"inherit","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2579-revision-v1","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-01 23:50:04","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 20:50:04","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"2579","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/2018\/01\/01\/2579-revision-v1\/","menu_order":"0","post_type":"revision","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2620","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-02 00:39:42","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 21:39:42","post_content":"<section class=\"ls section_padding_150\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<h2 class=\"section_header\">What is Physical Therapy?<\/h2>\n<p class=\"bottommargin_30 bold\">Physical therapy (or physiotherapy) seeks to relieve pain, restore, maintain and promote optimal physical function as well as limit disabilities resulting from injury or disease.<\/p>\n<p class=\"bottommargin_10\">Physical therapy utilizes a number of therapeutic methods, such as exercise therapy, manual therapy, electrotherapy also known as electrical physical agents (EPAs) such as laser, ultrasound, magnetic therapy, electrical stimulation as well as thermal agents of heat and cold. These agents are oftentimes referred to as modalities.<\/p>\n\n<h3>Physical Therapists<\/h3>\nThe Doctor of Physical Therapy (DPT) degree is entry-level and the only PT degree offered by schools in the United States. Graduates have an option to go into a residency and then a fellowship.\n\nAs doctoral level direct access clinicians, we conduct an examination process that includes: taking your history, conducting a systems review, and performing tests and measures to identify the problem.\n\nWe will refer you to a different medical specialist if we determine that the problems to be addressed warrant such a referral.\n\nIf the problem falls within our scope, we establish a diagnosis (we tell you what the problem is) and a prognosis (we tell you how long it will take to resolve it).\n<h3>Treatment<\/h3>\n<p class=\"bottommargin_10\">A comprehensive, tailored treatment plan is then created with a focus on your individual goals. Your therapist will utilize a range of treatment techniques to help you reach your goals.<\/p>\n\n<h3>Rehabilitation<\/h3>\nRehabilitation is a process which is dedicated to restoring, improving and maintaining physical strength and mobility, cognition and overall wellness. Rehabilitation involves specialists from many disciplines. We collaborate and communicate with many trusted and dedicated professionals in the area and we share a common goal of helping you achieve the highest level of function, independence, and quality of life possible.\n<blockquote class=\"no-border text-center\">\n<p class=\"highlight\">Need an appointment?<\/p>\n<a class=\"fw-btn fw-btn-1  color2\" href=\"contact.html\">Contact us<\/a><\/blockquote>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/section>","post_title":"Physical Rehabilitation","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"inherit","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2026-autosave-v1","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-02 00:39:42","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 21:39:42","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"2026","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/2018\/01\/02\/2026-autosave-v1\/","menu_order":"0","post_type":"revision","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2622","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-02 00:52:16","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 21:52:16","post_content":"<h1>Treatment<\/h1>\r\n<h3>1.Neck pain and headaches<\/h3>\r\nHeadaches can be caused by multiple issues and may be direct or referred in nature. Direct headaches will have their origin within your head and may relate to stress, chemical changes within your brain, food reactions, or other causes. Headaches can often be referred from your cervical spine (neck), your mid to upper back and your jaw. Referred headaches can often relate to poor posture, or inadequate flexibility or stability around the neck.\r\n\r\nRegardless of the potential issues at play, we specialize in thorough analysis and assessment. Our clinicians identify issues and develop treatment programs to deliver effective outcomes.\r\n\r\n<b>Common conditions :<\/b>\r\n\r\nThe head and neck are complex interrelated structures comprising intricate networks of discs, ligaments, vessels and vertebrae. As a result, there can be multiple factors contributing to head or neck pain. Some of the more common conditions we treat include post-surgical rehabilitation, disc problems, stiffness, facet joint dysfunction, neck related headaches, postural problems, acute sprains and strains, osteoarthritis and arm pain referring from the neck.\r\n<h3>2.Shoulder<\/h3>\r\nLike every patient we see, we treat every shoulder issue on a case by case basis. We tailor our approach to meet your specific individual needs. We\u2019ll obtain a full overview to determine the issue: the location and type of pain, the mechanism of injury, any aggravating factors, easing factors, contributing lifestyle factors, and your personal goals for rehabilitation. Then, we get to work.\r\n\r\n<b>Common conditions :<\/b>\r\n\r\nShoulder pain can be linked to a range of injuries, and resolution may require treatment to your shoulder, back and neck. Some of the more frequent conditions that present in clinic are postural dysfunctions or problems, post-surgical rehabilitation, tendon impingement, shoulder bursitis, acute joint soft tissue injuries, rotator cuff dysfunction, rotator cuff tears, AC joint injuries, and post-fracture rehabilitation.\r\n<h3>3.Elbow, wrist and hand<\/h3>\r\nPain, tingling or numbness around the elbow, wrist or hand can often be a sign of an overuse injury. These symptoms can be caused by a range of issues, but they\u2019re commonly associated with overloading tendons, muscles, and sometimes neural structures.\r\n\r\nOverloading can occur in sports and through biomechanical issues, but it frequently presents as an issue for office workers. Repetitive actions \u2013 performed day in, day out \u2013 can have an accumulative, damaging effect over the long term. Whether it\u2019s tennis-elbow, carpal tunnel or a trigger finger problem, pain and discomfort will impact upon your performance: both in sport and at the workplace.\r\n\r\n<b>Common conditions :<\/b>\r\n\r\nThere are many conditions that can affect the elbow, forearm and hand. Some of the more common issues we treat in clinic include tennis elbow, golfer\u2019s elbow, post-surgical rehabilitation, post-fracture rehabilitation, bursitis, post-dislocation rehabilitation, acute sprains and strains, postural problems, tendonitis, repetitive strain injuries, and reflex sympathetic dystrophy.\r\n<h3>4.Back<\/h3>\r\nBack pain can affect anyone and everyone. Regardless of your age, or whether you\u2019re an athlete or an office worker \u2013 or both \u2013 the back is a complex, nerve rich structure that is susceptible to a wide variety of issues.\r\n\r\nWe provide a range of treatments to manage your back pain, including manipulation, mobilization, massage, stretching, dry-needling and taping\/strapping. The essence of our clinic is to provide long term solutions, so postural reeducation and specific rehabilitation exercises form an important component of our treatment.\r\n\r\n<b>Common conditions:<\/b>\r\n\r\n<b>Posture<\/b>\u00a0: When we adopt certain postures over prolonged periods of time, the joints and tissues (muscles and ligaments) adapt into these postures by shortening and tightening, or lengthening and weakening. The way we sit or stand affects our joint position and our muscle length and strength.\r\n\r\n<b>Postural pain and dysfunction<\/b>: Prolonged or poor sitting can fatigue muscles, putting extra pressure on the joints, discs and nerves. Over-correcting a slouched posture will also cause pain by overworking the extensor muscles, compressing down on the joints and nerves in the spine and decreasing the abdominal muscle activity.\r\n\r\n<b>Disc problems<\/b>: Repetitive movements such as bending, or a sudden onset injury involving bending and twisting, can cause weakness or disruption of the fibrous ring on the outer surface of a disc. This allows the contents of the disc to push out of their natural location.Prolonged sitting such as office work and poor posture also puts strain on the back of the outer ring of the disc as the spine is held in a flexed and stretched position.\r\n\r\n<b>Nerve root pain<\/b>: This is often referred to as \u2018pinched nerve\u2019 or \u2018sciatica\u2019. True sciatica is compression of the sciatic nerve causing pain along the sciatic nerve into the leg. Compression can occur due to a disc bulge pressing on the nerve, or tight gluteal (buttock) muscles restricting the natural stretch of the sciatic nerve. Other nerves, apart from Sciatic, can also be affected. Each nerve root will tend to refer pain to a particular location. Sciatic will most commonly refer pain down the back of the leg to the outside of the calf and sometimes sole of the foot. Pinching of a root leading to the femoral nerve, however, will most likely refer pain into the groin or the front of the thigh.\r\n\r\nTrigger points or attenuated ligaments and tendons in the trunk can also refer pain into the buttocks or lower limbs. Referred pain can be described as throbbing, aching, or burning, pins and needles, or numbness.\r\n\r\n<b>Spondylolisthesis<\/b>: This is a term used when one vertebra has slipped out of place on the vertebra below. The slipping reduces the space in the spinal canal and narrows the hole where the nerve exits leading to stenosis. This can compress the nerve roots and cause referred pain, pins and needles, or numbness. The most common cause of the condition is general wear and tear leading to ligament lengthening and weakening , although it can also be caused by traumatic fractures or stress fractures.\r\n<h3>5.Hip and groin<\/h3>\r\nHip, groin and back pain can be closely related. It takes a thorough and highly skilled approach to identify the specific source of pain, alleviate the issue, and prevent it from recurring.\r\n\r\nThat\u2019s why our initial consultation is an extended one-hour appointment \u2013 to ensure that our experienced doctors have the time required to systematically assess issues and develop detailed, personal treatment plans for hip and groin pain.\r\n\r\nThrough careful analysis and assessment, we can identify your issue and any associated knock-on effects, relieve your pain, minimize your chance of recurrence and get you back to work, sport and your normal routine. That\u2019s the treat, cure, prevent approach in action.\r\n\r\n<b>Common conditions :<\/b>\r\n\r\nWe commonly treat a range of issues, including postural dysfunctions, post-surgical rehabilitation, post fracture rehabilitation, acute strains, labral or cartilage tears, muscle tears or muscular movement dysfunctions, and back pain referring into or related to the hip or groin.\r\n<h3>6.Knee<\/h3>\r\nKnee pain is a common and unwelcome symptom. It can present either through a direct injury, such as twisting of the joint while playing sport, or more gradually over time due to poor movement patterns, repeated loading, or congenital conditions.Our approach to treating knee pain is equally as broad. We tailor your individual treatment plan to suit your lifestyle and objectives.\r\n\r\n<b>Common conditions:<\/b>\r\n\r\nPost-surgical rehabilitation for ACL, patello-femoral syndrome, ITB syndrome, tendinopathies, acute ligament sprains and muscle strains, and meniscus injuries, and post fracture rehabilitation. We are also highly skilled at treating conditions that present with symptoms in the knee, but are related to the biomechanics of the foot and ankle, or hip, pelvis and trunk.\r\n<h3>7.Foot and ankle<\/h3>\r\nWhether your lifestyle is sporty or more subdued, foot pain is always unwelcome. We are perfectly equipped to identify and eliminate a range of foot and ankle injuries, to get you back in step with your regular routine. We can offer expert insight into a huge range of foot and ankle conditions, including those caused by acute injury, overuse, or ongoing biomechanical factors.\r\n\r\n<b>Common conditions :<\/b>\r\n\r\nThere are many issues that can affect the feet and ankles. Some of the more common issues we treat in clinic include Achilles tendon pain, plantar fasciitis, post-surgical rehabilitation, acute sprains and strains, tendinopathy, and calf tightness.","post_title":"Treatment","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"treatment","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-02 00:57:01","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 21:57:01","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"0","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/?page_id=2622","menu_order":"0","post_type":"page","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}
