{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2625","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-02 00:53:32","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 21:53:32","post_content":"<h3>Treatment<\/h3>\n <h3 class=\"fw-accordion-title\">Neck pain and headaches<\/h3>\n <p>Headaches can be caused by multiple issues and may be direct or referred in nature. Direct headaches will have their origin within your head and may relate to stress, chemical changes within your brain, food reactions, or other causes. Headaches can often be referred from your cervical spine (neck), your mid to upper back and your jaw. Referred headaches can often relate to poor posture, or inadequate flexibility or stability around the neck.\nRegardless of the potential issues at play, we specialize in thorough analysis and assessment. Our clinicians identify issues and develop treatment programs to deliver effective outcomes.\nCommon conditions :\nThe head and neck are complex interrelated structures comprising intricate networks of discs, ligaments, vessels and vertebrae. As a result, there can be multiple factors contributing to head or neck pain. Some of the more common conditions we treat include post-surgical rehabilitation, disc problems, stiffness, facet joint dysfunction, neck related headaches, postural problems, acute sprains and strains, osteoarthritis and arm pain referring from the neck.<\/p>\n <h3 class=\"fw-accordion-title\">Shoulder<\/h3>\n <p>Like every patient we see, we treat every shoulder issue on a case by case basis. We tailor our approach to meet your specific individual needs. We\u2019ll obtain a full overview to determine the issue: the location and type of pain, the mechanism of injury, any aggravating factors, easing factors, contributing lifestyle factors, and your personal goals for rehabilitation. Then, we get to work.\nCommon conditions :\nShoulder pain can be linked to a range of injuries, and resolution may require treatment to your shoulder, back and neck. Some of the more frequent conditions that present in clinic are postural dysfunctions or problems, post-surgical rehabilitation, tendon impingement, shoulder bursitis, acute joint soft tissue injuries, rotator cuff dysfunction, rotator cuff tears, AC joint injuries, and post-fracture rehabilitation.<\/p>\n\n<!-- 1abd9160c9b361c12b59474526f7eb46 -->","post_title":"Treatment","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"inherit","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2622-revision-v1","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-02 00:53:32","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 21:53:32","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"2622","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/2018\/01\/02\/2622-revision-v1\/","menu_order":"0","post_type":"revision","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}
{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2626","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-02 00:54:55","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 21:54:55","post_content":"<h3>Treatment<\/h3>\n <h3 class=\"fw-accordion-title\">Neck pain and headaches<\/h3>\n <p><p>Headaches can be caused by multiple issues and may be direct or referred in nature. Direct headaches will have their origin within your head and may relate to stress, chemical changes within your brain, food reactions, or other causes. Headaches can often be referred from your cervical spine (neck), your mid to upper back and your jaw. Referred headaches can often relate to poor posture, or inadequate flexibility or stability around the neck.<\/p>\n<p>\nRegardless of the potential issues at play, we specialize in thorough analysis and assessment. Our clinicians identify issues and develop treatment programs to deliver effective outcomes.<\/p>\nCommon conditions :\n<p>\nThe head and neck are complex interrelated structures comprising intricate networks of discs, ligaments, vessels and vertebrae. As a result, there can be multiple factors contributing to head or neck pain. Some of the more common conditions we treat include post-surgical rehabilitation, disc problems, stiffness, facet joint dysfunction, neck related headaches, postural problems, acute sprains and strains, osteoarthritis and arm pain referring from the neck.<\/p><\/p>\n <h3 class=\"fw-accordion-title\">Shoulder<\/h3>\n <p>Like every patient we see, we treat every shoulder issue on a case by case basis. We tailor our approach to meet your specific individual needs. We\u2019ll obtain a full overview to determine the issue: the location and type of pain, the mechanism of injury, any aggravating factors, easing factors, contributing lifestyle factors, and your personal goals for rehabilitation. Then, we get to work.\nCommon conditions :\nShoulder pain can be linked to a range of injuries, and resolution may require treatment to your shoulder, back and neck. Some of the more frequent conditions that present in clinic are postural dysfunctions or problems, post-surgical rehabilitation, tendon impingement, shoulder bursitis, acute joint soft tissue injuries, rotator cuff dysfunction, rotator cuff tears, AC joint injuries, and post-fracture rehabilitation.<\/p>\n\n<!-- 96c5f7ea7a51b60cfeb8261d4df4708a -->","post_title":"Treatment","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"inherit","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2622-revision-v1","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-02 00:54:55","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 21:54:55","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"2622","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/2018\/01\/02\/2622-revision-v1\/","menu_order":"0","post_type":"revision","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}
{"type":"row","data":{"table":"posts","row":{"ID":"2627","post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-02 00:56:58","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-01 21:56:58","post_content":"<h1>Treatment<\/h1>\n<h3>1.Neck pain and headaches<\/h3>\nHeadaches can be caused by multiple issues and may be direct or referred in nature. Direct headaches will have their origin within your head and may relate to stress, chemical changes within your brain, food reactions, or other causes. Headaches can often be referred from your cervical spine (neck), your mid to upper back and your jaw. Referred headaches can often relate to poor posture, or inadequate flexibility or stability around the neck.\n\nRegardless of the potential issues at play, we specialize in thorough analysis and assessment. Our clinicians identify issues and develop treatment programs to deliver effective outcomes.\n\n<b>Common conditions :<\/b>\n\nThe head and neck are complex interrelated structures comprising intricate networks of discs, ligaments, vessels and vertebrae. As a result, there can be multiple factors contributing to head or neck pain. Some of the more common conditions we treat include post-surgical rehabilitation, disc problems, stiffness, facet joint dysfunction, neck related headaches, postural problems, acute sprains and strains, osteoarthritis and arm pain referring from the neck.\n<h3>2.Shoulder<\/h3>\nLike every patient we see, we treat every shoulder issue on a case by case basis. We tailor our approach to meet your specific individual needs. We\u2019ll obtain a full overview to determine the issue: the location and type of pain, the mechanism of injury, any aggravating factors, easing factors, contributing lifestyle factors, and your personal goals for rehabilitation. Then, we get to work.\n\n<b>Common conditions :<\/b>\n\nShoulder pain can be linked to a range of injuries, and resolution may require treatment to your shoulder, back and neck. Some of the more frequent conditions that present in clinic are postural dysfunctions or problems, post-surgical rehabilitation, tendon impingement, shoulder bursitis, acute joint soft tissue injuries, rotator cuff dysfunction, rotator cuff tears, AC joint injuries, and post-fracture rehabilitation.\n<h3>3.Elbow, wrist and hand<\/h3>\nPain, tingling or numbness around the elbow, wrist or hand can often be a sign of an overuse injury. These symptoms can be caused by a range of issues, but they\u2019re commonly associated with overloading tendons, muscles, and sometimes neural structures.\n\nOverloading can occur in sports and through biomechanical issues, but it frequently presents as an issue for office workers. Repetitive actions \u2013 performed day in, day out \u2013 can have an accumulative, damaging effect over the long term. Whether it\u2019s tennis-elbow, carpal tunnel or a trigger finger problem, pain and discomfort will impact upon your performance: both in sport and at the workplace.\n\n<b>Common conditions :<\/b>\n\nThere are many conditions that can affect the elbow, forearm and hand. Some of the more common issues we treat in clinic include tennis elbow, golfer\u2019s elbow, post-surgical rehabilitation, post-fracture rehabilitation, bursitis, post-dislocation rehabilitation, acute sprains and strains, postural problems, tendonitis, repetitive strain injuries, and reflex sympathetic dystrophy.\n<h3>4.Back<\/h3>\nBack pain can affect anyone and everyone. Regardless of your age, or whether you\u2019re an athlete or an office worker \u2013 or both \u2013 the back is a complex, nerve rich structure that is susceptible to a wide variety of issues.\n\nWe provide a range of treatments to manage your back pain, including manipulation, mobilization, massage, stretching, dry-needling and taping\/strapping. The essence of our clinic is to provide long term solutions, so postural reeducation and specific rehabilitation exercises form an important component of our treatment.\n\n<b>Common conditions:<\/b>\n\n<b>Posture<\/b>\u00a0: When we adopt certain postures over prolonged periods of time, the joints and tissues (muscles and ligaments) adapt into these postures by shortening and tightening, or lengthening and weakening. The way we sit or stand affects our joint position and our muscle length and strength.\n\n<b>Postural pain and dysfunction<\/b>: Prolonged or poor sitting can fatigue muscles, putting extra pressure on the joints, discs and nerves. Over-correcting a slouched posture will also cause pain by overworking the extensor muscles, compressing down on the joints and nerves in the spine and decreasing the abdominal muscle activity.\n\n<b>Disc problems<\/b>: Repetitive movements such as bending, or a sudden onset injury involving bending and twisting, can cause weakness or disruption of the fibrous ring on the outer surface of a disc. This allows the contents of the disc to push out of their natural location.Prolonged sitting such as office work and poor posture also puts strain on the back of the outer ring of the disc as the spine is held in a flexed and stretched position.\n\n<b>Nerve root pain<\/b>: This is often referred to as \u2018pinched nerve\u2019 or \u2018sciatica\u2019. True sciatica is compression of the sciatic nerve causing pain along the sciatic nerve into the leg. Compression can occur due to a disc bulge pressing on the nerve, or tight gluteal (buttock) muscles restricting the natural stretch of the sciatic nerve. Other nerves, apart from Sciatic, can also be affected. Each nerve root will tend to refer pain to a particular location. Sciatic will most commonly refer pain down the back of the leg to the outside of the calf and sometimes sole of the foot. Pinching of a root leading to the femoral nerve, however, will most likely refer pain into the groin or the front of the thigh.\n\nTrigger points or attenuated ligaments and tendons in the trunk can also refer pain into the buttocks or lower limbs. Referred pain can be described as throbbing, aching, or burning, pins and needles, or numbness.\n\n<b>Spondylolisthesis<\/b>: This is a term used when one vertebra has slipped out of place on the vertebra below. The slipping reduces the space in the spinal canal and narrows the hole where the nerve exits leading to stenosis. This can compress the nerve roots and cause referred pain, pins and needles, or numbness. The most common cause of the condition is general wear and tear leading to ligament lengthening and weakening , although it can also be caused by traumatic fractures or stress fractures.\n<h3>5.Hip and groin<\/h3>\nHip, groin and back pain can be closely related. It takes a thorough and highly skilled approach to identify the specific source of pain, alleviate the issue, and prevent it from recurring.\n\nThat\u2019s why our initial consultation is an extended one-hour appointment \u2013 to ensure that our experienced doctors have the time required to systematically assess issues and develop detailed, personal treatment plans for hip and groin pain.\n\nThrough careful analysis and assessment, we can identify your issue and any associated knock-on effects, relieve your pain, minimize your chance of recurrence and get you back to work, sport and your normal routine. That\u2019s the treat, cure, prevent approach in action.\n\n<b>Common conditions :<\/b>\n\nWe commonly treat a range of issues, including postural dysfunctions, post-surgical rehabilitation, post fracture rehabilitation, acute strains, labral or cartilage tears, muscle tears or muscular movement dysfunctions, and back pain referring into or related to the hip or groin.\n<h3>6.Knee<\/h3>\nKnee pain is a common and unwelcome symptom. It can present either through a direct injury, such as twisting of the joint while playing sport, or more gradually over time due to poor movement patterns, repeated loading, or congenital conditions.Our approach to treating knee pain is equally as broad. We tailor your individual treatment plan to suit your lifestyle and objectives.\n\n<b>Common conditions:<\/b>\n\nPost-surgical rehabilitation for ACL, patello-femoral syndrome, ITB syndrome, tendinopathies, acute ligament sprains and muscle strains, and meniscus injuries, and post fracture rehabilitation. We are also highly skilled at treating conditions that present with symptoms in the knee, but are related to the biomechanics of the foot and ankle, or hip, pelvis and trunk.\n<h3>7.Foot and ankle<\/h3>\nWhether your lifestyle is sporty or more subdued, foot pain is always unwelcome. We are perfectly equipped to identify and eliminate a range of foot and ankle injuries, to get you back in step with your regular routine. We can offer expert insight into a huge range of foot and ankle conditions, including those caused by acute injury, overuse, or ongoing biomechanical factors.\n\n<b>Common conditions :<\/b>\n\nThere are many issues that can affect the feet and ankles. Some of the more common issues we treat in clinic include Achilles tendon pain, plantar fasciitis, post-surgical rehabilitation, acute sprains and strains, tendinopathy, and calf tightness.","post_title":"Treatment","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"inherit","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"2622-autosave-v1","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-02 00:56:58","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-01 21:56:58","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":"2622","guid":"http:\/\/rehab\/2018\/01\/02\/2622-autosave-v1\/","menu_order":"0","post_type":"revision","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0"}}}

This incorporates medical history, physical examination, and medical tests like MRIs, x-rays or ultrasound (depending on the patient and issue). Our doctor will be able to determine diagnosis and create a treatment plan. If required, we can recommend you to a specialist for additional examination and insight.\n\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"vertical-tab3\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">How long will my recovery take?<\/h3>\nAcute low back pain or neck pain is usually treated very successfully within two or three sessions. Postoperative and chronic problems require a longer treatment time. Every case is different, and every person will respond to rehabilitation and treatment differently. You\u2019ll have a much better understanding of your recovery timeframe after meeting with one of our doctors; establishing a clear diagnosis and relating it to your unique goals.\n\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"vertical-tab4\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">What are the steps involved in treatment ?<\/h3>\nOne common component of treatment is manual therapy, which is used to regain normal joint mobility and to release tight or overactive muscle and connective tissue. This is essential in recapturing optimal tissue flexibility and joint fluidity.\n\n<b>In addition, treatment commonly includes:<\/b>\n<ul>\n \t<li>Dedicated rehabilitative exercises including postural corrective exercises.<\/li>\n \t<li>Ergonomic\/workplace condition assessment.<\/li>\n \t<li>Newest and cutting edge equipment like laser, ultrasound, electrical stimulation.<\/li>\n \t<li>Recommendations for ongoing improvement.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"vertical-tab5\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">What can I do in the meantime if I\u2019m suffering from pain or loss of function?<\/h3>\nAvoid any activity that aggravates the affected area. We've Got Answers!<\/h2>\r\nAnswers to the most frequently asked questions.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div class=\"row vertical-tabs\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-5\">\r\n\r\n<!-- Nav tabs -->\r\n<ul class=\"nav\" role=\"tablist\">\r\n \t<li class=\"active\"><a role=\"tab\" href=\"faq2.html#vertical-tab1\" data-toggle=\"tab\">Why Us?<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li><a role=\"tab\" href=\"faq2.html#vertical-tab2\" data-toggle=\"tab\">How are my problems diagnosed?<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li><a role=\"tab\" href=\"faq2.html#vertical-tab3\" data-toggle=\"tab\">How long will my recovery take?<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li><a role=\"tab\" href=\"faq2.html#vertical-tab4\" data-toggle=\"tab\">What are the steps involved in treatment ?<\/a><\/li>\r\n \t<li><a role=\"tab\" href=\"faq2.html#vertical-tab5\" data-toggle=\"tab\">What can I do in the meantime if I\u2019m suffering from pain or loss of function?<\/a><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-7\">\r\n\r\n<!-- Tab panes -->\r\n<div class=\"tab-content no-border\">\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab1\" class=\"tab-pane fade in active\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">Why Us?<\/h3>\r\nWe are a team of orthopaedic Physical Therapists dedicated to quality care. We are privileged to be located in one office space with two orthopaedic surgeons and a Doctor of Podiatric Medicine with whom we cooperate very closely to ensure that your rehabilitative and therapeutic needs are fully met. We also have a professional relationship with doctors specializing in Pain Management. This ensures a comprehensive orthopaedic and rehabilitative care.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab2\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">How are my problems diagnosed?<\/h3>\r\nDiagnosis involves a careful, comprehensive assessment. This incorporates medical history, physical examination, and medical tests like MRIs, x-rays or ultrasound (depending on the patient and issue). Our doctor will be able to determine diagnosis and create a treatment plan. If required, we can recommend you to a specialist for additional examination and insight.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab3\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">How long will my recovery take?<\/h3>\r\nAcute low back pain or neck pain is usually treated very successfully within two or three sessions. Postoperative and chronic problems require a longer treatment time. Every case is different, and every person will respond to rehabilitation and treatment differently. You\u2019ll have a much better understanding of your recovery timeframe after meeting with one of our doctors; establishing a clear diagnosis and relating it to your unique goals.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab4\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">What are the steps involved in treatment ?<\/h3>\r\nOne common component of treatment is manual therapy, which is used to regain normal joint mobility and to release tight or overactive muscle and connective tissue. This is essential in recapturing optimal tissue flexibility and joint fluidity.\r\n\r\n<b>In addition, treatment commonly includes:<\/b>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Dedicated rehabilitative exercises including postural corrective exercises.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Ergonomic\/workplace condition assessment.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Newest and cutting edge equipment like laser, ultrasound, electrical stimulation.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Recommendations for ongoing improvement.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab5\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">What can I do in the meantime if I\u2019m suffering from pain or loss of function?<\/h3>\r\nAvoid any activity that aggravates the affected area. Get in touch with your doctor or with one of our doctors as soon as possible to book a detailed assessment.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab6\" class=\"tab-pane fade\"><\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab8\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<\/section>","post_title":"FAQ","post_excerpt":"Hamburger frankfurter pork loin kevin bacon Shank salami tenderloin ribeye, bresaola spare ribs capicola ball tip porchetta prosciutto. We are privileged to be located in one office space with two orthopaedic surgeons and a Doctor of Podiatric Medicine with whom we cooperate very closely to ensure that your rehabilitative and therapeutic needs are fully met. We also have a professional relationship with doctors specializing in Pain Management. This ensures a comprehensive orthopaedic and rehabilitative care.<\/p>\n <h3 class=\"fw-accordion-title\">How are my problems diagnosed?<\/h3>\n <p>Diagnosis involves a careful, comprehensive assessment. This incorporates medical history, physical examination, and medical tests like MRIs, x-rays or ultrasound (depending on the patient and issue). Our doctor will be able to determine diagnosis and create a treatment plan. If required, we can recommend you to a specialist for additional examination and insight.<\/p>\n <h3 class=\"fw-accordion-title\">How long will my recovery take?<\/h3>\n <p>Acute low back pain or neck pain is usually treated very successfully within two or three sessions. Postoperative and chronic problems require a longer treatment time. Every case is different, and every person will respond to rehabilitation and treatment differently. You\u2019ll have a much better understanding of your recovery timeframe after meeting with one of our doctors; establishing a clear diagnosis and relating it to your unique goals.<\/p>\n <h3 class=\"fw-accordion-title\">What are the steps involved in treatment ?<\/h3>\n <p>One common component of treatment is manual therapy, which is used to regain normal joint mobility and to release tight or overactive muscle and connective tissue. This is essential in recapturing optimal tissue flexibility and joint fluidity.\nIn addition, treatment commonly includes:\nDedicated rehabilitative exercises including postural corrective exercises.\nErgonomic\/workplace condition assessment.\nNewest and cutting edge equipment like laser, ultrasound, electrical stimulation.\nRecommendations for ongoing improvement.<\/p>\n\n<!-- 5e375b9586e5c7b9427e9aec8a0c181f -->","post_title":"FAQ","post_excerpt":"Hamburger frankfurter pork loin kevin bacon Shank salami tenderloin ribeye, bresaola spare ribs capicola ball tip porchetta prosciutto. We are privileged to be located in one office space with two orthopaedic surgeons and a Doctor of Podiatric Medicine with whom we cooperate very closely to ensure that your rehabilitative and therapeutic needs are fully met. We also have a professional relationship with doctors specializing in Pain Management. This ensures a comprehensive orthopaedic and rehabilitative care. <\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"tab-pane fade\" id=\"vertical-tab2\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">How are my problems diagnosed?<\/h3>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p> Diagnosis  involves a careful, comprehensive assessment. This incorporates medical history, physical examination, and medical tests like MRIs, x-rays or ultrasound (depending on the patient and issue).  Our doctor will be able to determine diagnosis and create a treatment plan. If required, we can recommend you to a specialist for additional examination and insight.<\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"tab-pane fade\" id=\"vertical-tab3\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">How long will my recovery take?<\/h3>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Acute low back pain or neck pain is usually treated very successfully within two or three sessions. Postoperative and chronic problems require a longer treatment  time. Every case is different, and every person will respond to rehabilitation and treatment differently. You\u2019ll have a much better understanding of your recovery timeframe after meeting with one of our doctors; establishing a clear diagnosis and relating it to your unique goals.<\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"tab-pane fade\" id=\"vertical-tab4\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">What are the steps involved in treatment ?<\/h3>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>One common component of treatment is manual therapy, which is used to regain normal joint mobility and to release tight or overactive muscle and connective tissue. This is essential in recapturing optimal tissue flexibility and joint fluidity.<\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><b>In addition, treatment commonly includes:<\/b><\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><ul>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li>Dedicated rehabilitative exercises including postural corrective exercises.<\/li>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li>Ergonomic\/workplace condition assessment.<\/li>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li>Newest and cutting edge equipment like laser, ultrasound, electrical stimulation. <\/li>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li>Recommendations for ongoing improvement.<\/li>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/ul><\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"tab-pane fade\" id=\"vertical-tab5\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">What can I do in the meantime if I\u2019m suffering from pain or loss of function?<\/h3>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Avoid any activity that aggravates the affected area. Get in touch with your doctor or with one of our doctors  as soon as possible to book a detailed assessment.<\/p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"tab-pane fade\" id=\"vertical-tab6\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">Justo duo dolores et ea rebum?<\/h3>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. We are privileged to be located in one office space with two orthopaedic surgeons and a Doctor of Podiatric Medicine with whom we cooperate very closely to ensure that your rehabilitative and therapeutic needs are fully met. We also have a professional relationship with doctors specializing in Pain Management. This ensures a comprehensive orthopaedic and rehabilitative care.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab2\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">How are my problems diagnosed?<\/h3>\r\nDiagnosis involves a careful, comprehensive assessment. This incorporates medical history, physical examination, and medical tests like MRIs, x-rays or ultrasound (depending on the patient and issue). Our doctor will be able to determine diagnosis and create a treatment plan. If required, we can recommend you to a specialist for additional examination and insight.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab3\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">How long will my recovery take?<\/h3>\r\nAcute low back pain or neck pain is usually treated very successfully within two or three sessions. Postoperative and chronic problems require a longer treatment time. Every case is different, and every person will respond to rehabilitation and treatment differently. You\u2019ll have a much better understanding of your recovery timeframe after meeting with one of our doctors; establishing a clear diagnosis and relating it to your unique goals.\r\n\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab4\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">What are the steps involved in treatment ?<\/h3>\r\nOne common component of treatment is manual therapy, which is used to regain normal joint mobility and to release tight or overactive muscle and connective tissue. This is essential in recapturing optimal tissue flexibility and joint fluidity.\r\n\r\n<b>In addition, treatment commonly includes:<\/b>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Dedicated rehabilitative exercises including postural corrective exercises.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Ergonomic\/workplace condition assessment.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Newest and cutting edge equipment like laser, ultrasound, electrical stimulation.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Recommendations for ongoing improvement.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div id=\"vertical-tab5\" class=\"tab-pane fade\">\r\n<h3 class=\"topmargin_0\">What can I do in the meantime if I\u2019m suffering from pain or loss of function?<\/h3>\r\nAvoid any activity that aggravates the affected area.
